title: banana bread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs using electric mixer. Add milk and bananas. Add dry ingredients.
Mix in nuts by hand.
Place in 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Add tomato sauce, water, tomato paste, salt, garlic, onion, pepper and oregano. Simmer until thick, about 20 minutes.

title: ham and cheese bites
directions: Mix together cheese and onions.
Spread on ham.
Roll slices like jelly roll.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Cut each slice into 8 pieces.

title: granny stallings apple salad(very old)
directions: Dice apples; add pineapple chunks, grated cheese and nuts.

title: cholesterol-free lemon pound cake
directions: Cream margarine until light and fluffy.
Add sugar gradually. Add Egg Beaters (thawed out), one third at a time, not all at once. Add lemon peel and vanilla and almond flavorings; add dry ingredients in two parts.
Gradually add milk, then add rest of flour.
Mix 2 more minutes.
Turn into greased and floured loaf pans.
If you use 1 pan, bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes (Bundt pan).
If you use 2 loaf pans, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate marshmallow squares
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a 3-quart glass bowl.
Microwave on Medium (50% power) for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes or until morsels are softened, stirring after 2 minutes.

title: pork barbecue (oak lawn fest)
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients until brown sugar is melted.
Marinate pork cubes for 2 to 3 hours, best overnight.
Cook over charcoal using wooden skewers.
May use pineapple chunks and green peppers on skewers too.

title: wendy's deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs for a full 10 minutes. Take off stove immediately and immerse into ice cold water. Peel immediately. Let

eggs cool. Cut eggs according to how you would like them to look. Remove yellows to bowl. Beat yellows with electric beaters while adding Braswell's mayo. Once yellows are smooth, then add remaining ingredients. Lastly, smooth this
mixture into the whites and serve cool.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix with melted margarine, vanilla and 2 eggs. Mixture will be thick.
Working with fingers, pack in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs; this will be thin.
Pour over top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for exactly 40 minutes.
Don't peek in. Take cake out of oven and let cool 4 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: make ahead breakfast
directions: Put together bread, cheese and ham in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour over layers.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Melt 1 stick of oleo and drizzle over mixture before baking.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Lightly butter slices of bread.
Place buttered side down in skillet.
Add dressing, cheese, corned beef and kraut.
Grill until golden brown.
Serve open face or closed.

title: chocolate kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together with vanilla.
Add flour gradually until well blended.
Stir in pecans. Chill the dough.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Refrigerate until serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken rice bake
directions: Mix rice, soups and juice.
Put in a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Lay chicken on top.
Pour butter over top.
Sprinkle with almonds and cheese.
Cover with foil; bake 2 1/2 hours at 275°. Remove foil last 1/2 hour.

title: haystacks
directions: Brown hamburger; add Ragu and taco seasoning.
Put on plate in order listed.

title: peanut butter creams
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips; mix until well blended.
Remove from bowl and knead on board until smooth. Spread and pat into 9-inch square pan.
Melt chocolate chips over low heat.
Spread over peanut butter mixture.
Cool until chocolate is firm, about 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Makes 64 pieces.

title: cool salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese, pineapple and nuts together. Sprinkle dry jello over mixture.
Toss and refrigerate.
Can be served immediately.
Strawberries and strawberry jello can be used in place of pineapple and lime jello.
Both are good and very colorful, especially at Christmas.
Also low calorie.

title: best buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in buttered flavored Crisco.
Add and stir in buttermilk.
Knead 1/2 minute. Roll 3/8-inch thick.
Cut and brush with oil.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: butterscotch fudge(microwave)
directions: In 2 1/2-quart casserole, combine sugar, butter and milk. Cook at High for 9 to 11 minutes or until sugar is dissolved. Stir twice.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until butterscotch is melted.
Turn into well-greased 12 x 8-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares to serve.
Yield:
3 pounds.

title: meat cabbage rolls
directions: Dip cabbage leaves in hot water until wilted; drain.
Combine meat, salt, pepper, rice and garlic; mix well.
Place 2 tablespoons of meat mixture in each cabbage leaf.
Roll leaf around meat and fasten with toothpick.
Place sauerkraut in bottom of pan.
Lay rolls on top.
Pour tomato soup and tomato paste over all.
Add enough water to cover.
Cook slowly for 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Poke holes in clean potatoes.
Butter potato on outside.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 2 hours.

title: ham jambalaya(great for leftover ham.)
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oil until tender.
Add bouillon diluted with 1 soup can water, rice and ham.
Cover and cook slowly 30 minutes.
A good quick skillet meal the whole family will like.

title: date squares
directions: Blend together the brown sugar and shortening.
Add, one at a time, the eggs; beat well.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Add the flour mixture to sugar and egg mixture; add dates, nuts and cherries.
Bake in large pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Arrange layers of orange sections in serving dish and sprinkle with sugar and coconut.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, topping with coconut.
Chill before serving.
Serves 6.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix sugar, flour and beer. Pour mixture into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven. Make slits across top with sharp knife.
Pour butter mixture on top.
Continue baking 15 more minutes.
Done when knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: delicious dessert
directions: In the early Spring, pick Blue Elder flowerets. These are pale yellow when first in bloom.
Place in pail of water for a few hours or wash carefully.
The flowers sometimes have tiny gnats in them.
Drain on paper towels.

title: hot dog relish(single recipe.  may be doubled.)
directions: Boil for 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup flour.
Make like a paste or thickening.
Cook until thick and can in jars (pints).
This is a sweet, thick, delicious relish.

title: coconut shrimp wontons
directions: Combine shrimp, coconut, cream cheese and 1/2 cup shrimp sauce in a mixing bowl. Place about 2 teaspoons shrimp mixture onto one corner of one won ton wrapper; moisten edges with water. Fold in half to form triangle; press firmly to seal. Repeat with remaining won ton wrappers and shrimp mixture.

title: raisin rock cookie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate.
Fold into cream cheese mixture with pecans.

title: veggie bars
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough.
Place in a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan, pressing edges and perforations together to line bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until browned.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer 1 minute or until smooth.
Spread over crust in pan.
Combine peppers and remaining ingredients; sprinkle over cream cheese mixture.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares. Yields 8 dozen.

title: raisins puffs
directions: Cook raisins and water until water is used up.
Set aside to cool.
Mix dough.
Add raisins mixture.
Mix well with spoon. Shape into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: sweet roll dough
directions: Measure 1 3/4 cups of flour into large bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat milk, water and shortening until 120° to 130°.
Pour into flour mixture.
Add eggs and beat with electric mixer at low speed for 1/2 minute.
Continue beating for 3 more minutes at high speed.
Stir in remainder of flour.
Dough will be soft and rather sticky.
Knead about 3 minutes, until smooth. Cover and let rest for 20 minutes, then shape as desired.
Let rise 40 to 60 minutes, until light.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: hummingbird cake deluxe
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt in large bowl.
Mix well. Add eggs and oil, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans, bananas and raisins.

Spoon into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cool in pans for 10 minutes. Remove to wire racks to cool completely. Spread frosting between layers and over top and side of cake.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup pecans.
Yields 12 servings.

title: heath bars
directions: Put crackers on foil-lined cookie sheet (not Teflon coated) end to end.
Melt butter slowly.
Add 1 cup sugar and bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Spread on crackers and bake in 350° oven for approximately 15 minutes.
Pour on chocolate chips, wait about a minute and spread around. Sprinkle with pecans.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll out sugar cookie dough into a large circle. Put on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 12-14 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool.
Spread with cream cheese that has been thinned with a little milk. Arrange chunks, wedges, or slices of fresh or canned fruit that has been
drained.
Glaze with one cup of pineapple juice thickened with 2 Tbsp. cornstarch.

title: tamale pie
directions: Lightly brown ground beef; drain off excess grease.
Add onion and pepper and 3 tablespoons shortening and lightly cook, don't brown. Add all other ingredients.
Mix well and place in a greased baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Layer pie plate with Muenster cheese.
Mix well-drained spinach, Ricotta cheese and spices together.
Pour over cheese layer.
Add additional layer of Muenster cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: succotash(fresh shell beans)
directions: If using fresh shell beans, add water to cover.
Mix all ingredients and simmer over low heat until beans are very soft and liquid is nearly gone and slightly thickened.

title: beer margaritas
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender. Add ice to fill.
Pulse until mixture is blended and slushy.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples and spread in buttered 9-inch square baking pan.
Mix sifted flour with sugar and cinnamon. Cut butter or margarine into flour and sugar mixture.
Spread crumb mixture over apple slices and bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: *For a softer, rounder cookie, add 1/4 cup more flour.

title: scalloped (cream style) corn
directions: Mix eggs with yolks. Mix together flour and sugar. Mix all together and bake at 350° for at least 1 hour or until done.

title: sole veronique
directions: Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper; place in a large skillet with butter, shallots and wine.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove fish to a heatproof serving dish.
Keep warm.
Continue cooking liquid in skillet on high heat, uncovered, until reduced to about 1/2 cup.
Remove from heat and, if desired, strain.
Add to Cream Sauce and check seasoning.
Fold in whipped cream.
Place grapes around fish and pour sauce over all.
Place under broiler until browned, about 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and milk.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: blueberry-ricotta squares
directions: In a small mixer bowl combine the flour, the 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add the milk, shortening, the 1 egg and the 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed until combined.
Beat on medium speed for 1 minute.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; spread evenly.
Sprinkle blueberries over batter.

title: easy punch
directions: *One quart sherbet may be substituted for orange juice.

title: deacon jim's chicken
directions: Cube chicken; brown in margarine.
Set aside.
In same pan, cook onions and pepper.
Add to chicken.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings; heat.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Cover; simmer about 35 minutes, adding wine during simmering.
Serve over angel hair pasta or linguine.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients except peaches.
Pour in baking dish.
Put peaches on top of batter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and poppy seed in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and flavorings.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: beef roast and gravy
directions: Combine soups and seasonings.
Mix well. Place roast in roasting pan. Pour soup mixture over roast.
Cover well.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
This can be served over rice or creamed potatoes.

title: mushrooms a la pancetta
directions: Trim the stems of the mushrooms and wipe them to remove sand, but avoid washing them, if possible.
Cut the largest ones in half.
Chop the bacon or Pancetta into small pieces.
Melt the shortening in a skillet and add the chopped bacon.
Saute the bacon and sprinkle with pepper.
Add the mushrooms and cook them over a low heat for 1 1/2 hours or until the liquid has evaporated.
Add the garlic and parsley and cook for another 5 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli until crisp. Mix butter with dressing/crackers for topping. Mix all ingredients and add topping. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: "the next best thing to robert redford"
directions: Prepare bottom crust by mixing flour, butter and pecans until crumblike.
Press mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly golden; cool.

title: salad
directions: Pour hot water over marshmallows.
Add Jell-O and stir thoroughly.
Cool until firm.
Add whipping cream, cottage cheese, pineapple and pecans.
Place in refrigerator.
May make this the night before it will be used.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add alternately flour mixture and buttermilk to creamed mixture, adding the flour at the first and last.
Fold in fresh apples. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given. Roll small amount of dough and cut out. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: dilly beans
directions: Wash beans; snap ends off.
Stick them in canning jars whole with dill on bottom of jar.
Heat vinegar and water with spices. Boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour liquid over beans, leaving air space at top of jar.
Seal.
Put jars in boiling water to cover.
Leave 1 hour.
Makes 4 pints.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together sugars and flour.
Mix eggs (unbeaten), milk, vanilla and margarine.
Combine all ingredients and mix with low speed mixer.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Pie will shake firm and not wobble when done.

title: lemonade salad
directions: Put crushed Ritz crackers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Eagle Brand milk, lemonade, crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.
Spread over cracker crumbs.

title: pineapple chiffon cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into small bowl.
Make well in center.
In this order, add oil, egg yolks and pineapple juice.
Beat until satin smooth.
In large bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until very stiff.
Pour egg yolk batter over egg whites, folding gently.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost with Fake Whip Cream Frosting with drained crushed pineapple added.
Cake may be split for frosting in center.

title: sue's appetizers
directions: Spread soup on bread; cut in 4 pieces.
Place water chestnuts in center of bread.
Fold bread over and wrap bacon around it. Bake for 30 minutes or until bacon is done.
Turn after 15 minutes.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Bring to a boil, cover and simmer.

title: sunset salad
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water.
Add pineapple with juice and lemon juice.
Add carrots and pour into bowl or molds. Chill until set, about 1 hour.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook in a large stockpot until desired thickness. Can in sterilized jars.

title: cherry-fruit pie *
directions: Add cornstarch to juices and water.
Cook on medium heat until thick and clear, 10 to 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add sugar and stir; add cherries and pineapple, set aside to cool or place in freezer for 5 minutes. When slightly set, add bananas and nuts. Pour into baked pie shells and chill several hours.
Top with whipped cream to serve.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place
layers
in vegetables in order given in a crock-pot. Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Put ground beef on
top. Mix
tomato
soup
and
water;
pour into crock-pot. Cover and set on high for 2 to 4 hours or low 6 to 8 hours.

title: light fettuccini alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccini, drain and cover to keep warm. Melt butter in large skillet over low heat. Stir in flour, pepper, and nutmeg. Gradually stir in Half-and-Half. Cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until mixture thickens slightly, stirring frequently. Remove from heat and add drained fettuccini, Parmesan cheese and chopped parsley. Blend Well. Yields 8 servings.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Drain juice from these two ground-up ingredients, add pepper ingredients to the liquid and bring to a rolling boil.
Cool to lukewarm and add one small bottle of Certo.
Stir well and pour into glasses.

title: scalloped crab
directions: Arrange in a large greased casserole (1 1/2 quart or 9 inch square baking pan) a layer of crab.
Sprinkle generously with cracker crumbs and dot with butter and season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Repeat layers until all crab and crackers are used.
Then add milk to moisten well.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve with lemon.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Beat well eggs and sugar.
Add melted oleo and vanilla.
Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Mix all together; add coconut and walnuts.
Put on cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
As soon as cake is removed from oven spread Marshmallow Creme on top, then frost.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook 1 pound spaghetti in boiling water until tender, but still firm.
Immediately rinse in cold water and drain well. Place in a large bowl.
Add 8 ounces of garlic and herb dressing and desired amount of the ingredients listed.
Mix well.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix butter, sugar, egg yolks and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt.
Press evenly in bottom of pan.
Bake until delicately browned, 25 to 35 minutes (crust will be soft).
Remove from oven; immediately sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Let stand until soft; spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
While warm, cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Yields 32 bars.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except Ritz crackers.
Place in a baking dish.
Crush a tube of Ritz crackers on pineapple mixture.
Cut 1 stick of butter on crackers.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake white cake mix as directed in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool. Poke 25 to 30 holes in cake with the end of a wooden spoon.
Pour cream of coconut over and let it soak.
Top with whipped cream and then sprinkle with coconut.
Yummy!

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Gently fold in all other ingredients.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When cool, top with spoonful of Cool Whip before serving or make your favorite white icing.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Mix with soup.
Spread cream cheese on top.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onions, peppers and garlics in oil in a large dutch oven until tend; add next 9 ingredients and chicken.
Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat, simmer 1 hour.
Add tortillas and simmer 5 minutes.
Top with cheese in bowls.

title: wheat germ carrot layer cake
directions: Combine wheat germ, flours, brown sugar, cocoa, baking powder, cinnamon and salt in large bowl.
Stir to blend.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until evenly mixed.
Turn into 3 greased 8-inch round layer cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 22 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 5 minutes.
Invert onto racks to cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and roll in chopped pecans on plastic wrap.
Roll in plastic and refrigerate for 2 days.

title: raised waffles
directions: Put first 2 ingredients in large mixing bowl. Let stand 5 minutes.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Beat in flour.
Cover the bowl. Let stand overnight
or at least 8 hours (but not in refrigerator).
When time to cook the waffles, add last 2 ingredients.
Beat well.
The batter will be very thin.
Cook on a waffle iron.
Makes 6 or more large waffles.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine oil, sugar and spices.
Stir sauerkraut into oil mixture.
Add apples and grated carrots.
Toss to coat.
Very good with fried fish.
Serves 4.

title: corned beef goulash
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in small amount of water.
When done, add corned beef and corn. Heat.
This is a good camping dish, it stays hot.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Beat all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Mix those in and pour into Bundt pan which has been greased and dusted with cocoa. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put uncooked rice on bottom of pan. Mix water, soups and butter, then pour over rice and mix.
Add broccoli. Melt cheese and pour on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dip for veggies or chips
directions: Soften cream cheese. Blend with soup. Add garlic salt.

title: cashew brittle
directions: In an iron skillet, boil honey and water until it forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water.
Add nuts and continue to boil until brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Stir continuously.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and soda.
Mix well and pour onto a greased cookie sheet.
When cool, break into pieces.
Makes 1 pound.

title: graham cracker nut cake
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar.
Add
eggs,	one
at a time. Crumble crackers, add to mix.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 5 to 10 minutes.

title: headquarters chili
directions: Cook beef, green peppers, onions and garlic in oil in crock-pot until beef is lightly browned.
Add all ingredients except beans. Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir in undrained beans; cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: oven baked "southern fried" chicken
directions: Put Skinny Shake in heavy paper bag.
Moisten the chicken pieces with water and shake them up in the bag a few pieces at a time.
Arrange, skin side up in a single layer on a nonstick baking pan and bake in a moderate oven (375°) for about 45 minutes, adding absolutely no other fats or oils.
Don't be alarmed if the chicken seems dry for the first 20 minutes, then the Skinny Shake starts to work and at the end of the baking period, it will be crisp and perfect.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Boil peeled turnips in salted water.
Drain and mash well. Add butter, softened cream cheese and sugar.
Add more salt if needed.
Place in casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemonade pie #1
directions: Mix lemonade, milk, flavoring and Cool Whip. Pour into pie shells and chill.

title: banana and peanut butter shake
directions: That I'm not among the dead.
Though I'm getting more forgetful and mixed up in the head.
I got use to my arthritis, to my dentures I'm resigned.

I can manage my bifocals, but gosh I miss my mind, for sometimes I can't remember, when I stand at the foot of the stairs, if I must go up for something or have I just come down from there? And before the fridge so often, my poor mind is filled with doubt have I just put food away or have I come to take some out?

title: lena's meatball surprise
directions: Place all the ingredients, except ground beef, in kettle and cook until almost done.
Make the ground beef into small balls. Add it in the kettle.
Cook until done and dry.
You might have to drain some water off.

title: raisin loaf
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add mandarin peel and egg, beat until light and fluffy.
Mix flour, baking powder, and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture alternately with milk and mandarin juice. Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes, then turn out onto wire rack to cool.
When loaf is still slightly warm, spoon Mandarin Glaze over top.

title: cherry cream whip salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and condensed milk well in blender.
Empty into large bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until mixed well.
Place in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: blender fudge frosting
directions: Put milk and chocolate in blender.
Liquefy until smooth.
Add marshmallows, then process until smooth.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Combine ingredients except haddock and bring to a boil.
Drop in cut up fish.
Cook over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain and dribble melted butter over top.
Serve with rice.

title: mrs. fields cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients together and beat 3 to 4 minutes; add remaining ingredients.
Line cookie sheet with wax paper. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned. Cool 5 minutes on pan before removing.

title: fast casserole
directions: Mix French fries and ground beef.
Place in casserole dish and pour over cream of chicken soup.
Cook in oven at 350° about 30 minutes until meat is done.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Melt jelly and mustard together in saucepan over low heat. Slice wieners into bite-size pieces.
Add to sauce and heat thoroughly.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: cornmeal crepes with spiced plum compote
directions: Combine plums, sugar, cinnamon and cloves in small saucepan and cook over medium heat until soft and thickened, about 20 to 30 minutes, depending on ripeness of plums.
Remove from heat and let cool. When cool, spread about 1/4 cup plum compote over crepe, then fold crepe in quarters.
Sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar.
Place on baking sheet and glaze under broiler 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican corn pie
directions: Grease a 10-inch pie plate generously with shortening.
In a large bowl, beat eggs. Add remaining ingredients and stir until thoroughly mixed. Pour into pie plate and bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: cranberry apple casserole
directions: Mix and put the ingredients in a casserole dish.

title: fred's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Place crescent rolls in a pie pan to make the crust.
Bake per instructions.
Saute onions in butter; brown meat and drain.
Add barbecue sauce and ketchup to meat.
Add meat sauce to baked crust, top with cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: strawberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Pour into pan.
Mix together sugar, flour and milk in a bowl.
Pour strawberries on top of butter.
Pour mixture on top of strawberries.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: dog breath biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, cornmeal, mint and parsley in a large bowl.
Add oil and water and mix.
Roll out to 1/4 inch thickness onto floured surface and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake for 40 minutes or until lightly brown.
Turn heat off and let biscuits dry out in oven for several hours.
Store in fridge in airtight container.
Your dog will love them!

title: hush puppies
directions: Stir first six ingredients together until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Select a 7 or 8 pound brisket and cover with half bottle of Sidney vinegar and oil dressing.
Bake at 250° for about 4 hours. Refrigerate until ready to slice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Add all ingredients together in a big bowl; stir and stir.
Store in refrigerator.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, cheese, Bisquick and seasonings well.
Beat egg and oil together.
Pour over squash mixture and blend well. Pour into greased casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: golden meatball casserole
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, egg and salt.
Mix lightly.
Shape into 18 meatballs.
Brown in small amount of oil on all sides in large skillet.
Drain.
Add water, rice, carrots, green peppers and onion.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Add cheese and heat until cheese is melted.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: crepes
directions: Mix all ingredients (thin batter); pour into pan (I use 6-inch cast-iron skillet), sprayed with Pam.
Pour small amount in center of pan, then tilt pan so batter covers entire surface.
Remove when top looks dry.
Do not flip (brown just 1 side).
Fill with favorite fillings.
I use pie fillings.
Place 2 tablespoons in center through diameter, then roll or wrap up.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients to form a thick batter.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add batter to form pancakes.
Fry until golden brown and slightly firm.

title: fantastic chicken
directions: Mix soup mix, preserves and dressing together.
Place chicken breasts in an 8 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour mixture on top of chicken and cover the dish with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sticky chicken
directions: Place chicken in a flat baking dish.
Mix ingredients together.
Spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Add sauce to ground beef; simmer 15 minutes.
Combine soup and chilies with 1/2 can water; set aside.
Alternate layers in dish of tortillas, meat sauce, soup mixture and cheese.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients into pot and heat until butter melts. Refrigerate after cooling.
Shake well before using.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Remove seeds if using whole chilies and cut into strips.
(Do not touch your eyes after touching any chilies, can cause severe eye irritation.) Mix together eggs, milk, flour and salt.
Start layering ingredients into your casserole dish.
I start with a layer of cheese, chilies, cheese, chilies and end with cheese.
Pour egg mixture over top; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Should be browned on top. Serve with tacos, enchiladas or Spanish rice.
Easy and good dish.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onions, garlic, salt, pepper, chili powder and oregano.
Add tomato paste and tomatoes; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on box.
Layer noodles, meat and cheeses until all ingredients are used.
Lasagna should be sprinkled with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
You may want to cover with foil for the last 10 minutes to prevent overbrowning.
Freezes well.

title: cucumber dip
directions: While draining cucumbers (on paper towels), beat cream cheese and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well, adding cucumbers last. Refrigerate overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Serve as a vegetable dip or as a filling for finger sandwiches.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; roll into balls.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Add barbecue sauce, Kraft honey and onion. Stir into meat balls.
Serve warm.

title: quick brownies
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 9-inch pan in oven at 375°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add unbeaten eggs.
Pour in melted oleo.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°, using the pan in which oleo was melted.
No flouring is necessary.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: In large pot, combine onion, meat and garlic; cook until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Skim off excess fat; add remaining ingredients and water.
Simmer, uncovered, 3 hours or until sauce is thick.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: self-crust chicken pie
directions: Cook, skin and debone chicken.
Cut into small pieces.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Slice eggs and place on top of chicken.
Mix broth, soup and vegetables and pour on top of chicken and eggs.
Combine melted butter, flour, milk and pepper. Pour onto chicken.
Do not stir for this makes the crust.
Cook in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: pineapple icebox pudding
directions: Place marshmallows, jello and sugar into microwave and melt; cool but don't let set.
Whip cream; add pineapple and nuts and mix with cooled marshmallow mixture.
Crush wafers and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over this.
Add remaining crumbs on top. Set in refrigerator until firm.

title: homemade bisquick
directions: Stir baking powder, salt and cream of tartar into the flour. Cut in shortening and mix until like cornmeal.
Store in airtight container at room temperature.
Keeps about 6 weeks and may be used for anything Bisquick is used for.

title: biscuit stuffing on chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown pork chops in oil.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine 1 can cream soup, celery, onion, egg and seasonings.
Separate cans of biscuits into 10 biscuits; cut each biscuit into 8 pieces.
Stir into soup mixture; spoon over meat.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until meat is tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Combine flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Dip eggplant into egg, then into flour mixture.
Brown eggplant, half at a time, in the hot oil, adding additional oil as needed.
Drain well on paper towel.
Using half the eggplant, place in a single layer in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with half of the Parmesan.
Top with half the sauce and half the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, cut remaining Mozzarella cheese in triangles and place on top. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot.
Serves 6.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Mix eggs, milk and sugars together.
Add melted butter and rest of ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 35 minutes.
Real good.

title: fudge sauce
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add butter, salt and boiling water; mix well.
Bring to boiling point while stirring.
Lower heat, but keep bubbly.
Stir constantly.
Cook for 4 to 5 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.
Enjoy.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Chop shrimp.
Heat tomato soup and cream cheese in top of double boiler until cream cheese melts.
Cool slightly.
Stir in gelatin and mix well.
Add shrimp, mayonnaise, celery, pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased 1 1/2-quart mold (use fish-shaped).
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Serve with crackers.
Makes about 50 appetizer servings.

title: greek walnut cake
directions: Beat yolks, add sugar and beat.
Mix other ingredients; add to eggs.
Add vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites and turn into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: cookies in a jar
directions: Variations:
Instead of the M & M's or chocolate chips, substitute raisins, snipped dried fruit (apricots, prunes) chopped pecans or English walnuts.

title: yummy cheese ball
directions: Grind cheese and cream cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika or roll with nuts.
Makes 2 balls.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute
first
4 ingredients in water to slightly cover. Add remaining ingredients and simmer until flavors are blended.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Combine dry ingredients.
Blend in shortening.
Stir in yeast and remaining water.
Let rise until double in size, about 2 hours.
Form into small balls.
Put 3 in each muffin pan.
Let rise again until double in size.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chop suey
directions: Dip beef, pork, veal (chop suey meat) in flour; fry until dark brown.
Add celery and onions and cook until well done.
Add soy sauce and cook in oven for 2 hours.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Add 1 can soy bean sprouts 1/2 hour before serving.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Cook noodles, drain and pat dry.
Cook shrimp in soup; add a little milk if too thick.
Mix together cottage cheese, cream cheese, onion and Parmesan cheese.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Layer 1/2 of the noodles, 1/3 of the cheese mixture and 1/3 of the shrimp mixture.
Repeat, ending with soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stop here if making ahead! Sprinkle 2 cups shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Slice tomato on top and bake 20 to 30 minutes more until bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: irish bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and butter with fingers.
Add raisins, caraway seed and baking powder; mix again. Form a well in the mixture and pour eggs and milk into it.
Fold until mixture is completely folded in.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle with equal parts of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake for 1 hour.
Cool for 30 minutes before removing from pan.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients, then add flour, eggs and vanilla.
Then cream these all together and put into greased Bundt pan.
Cook for 1 hour on 300°.

title: new orleans style calas
directions: Combine rice, eggs, vanilla and nutmeg, mixing well.
Sift sugar, salt, flour and baking powder together and add to the rice mixture.
Thoroughly mix and drop by spoonfuls into vegetable oil heated to 360°.
Fry until brown on all sides.
Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towel.
Keep warm while frying all calas.
Serve sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Serves 6.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk.
Combine beans, mushrooms and 3/4 of the onions.
Mix with soup mixture in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes; ten minutes before casserole is done, sprinkle with remaining onion rings.

title: turkey hawaiian
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, cook onion in butter or margarine until tender, but not brown.
Stir in peas, celery, mushrooms, chicken broth, the 3/4 cup water and soy sauce.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add syrup to saucepan; bring mixture to boiling; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir cornstarch into the 1/4 cup water; add to saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Add turkey, pineapple, and water chestnuts; heat through.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Pass additional soy sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: three grain pancakes
directions: Measure all dry ingredients and put in a bowl.
Beat egg slightly with oil and milk.
Add to dry mixture.
Drop by a big spoon onto hot greased griddle.
(Use Pam spray or a little olive oil.)

title: marie's-chile's eggs
directions: Layer chiles, cheese and eggs in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Sprinkle seasoning salt on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (first 15 minutes covered with foil).

title: beer bread
directions: Combine water, beer and oil in saucepan.
Heat to 120° to 130°.
Set aside.
Combine 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt in large mixing bowl.
Add preceding liquid and beat 5 minutes. Gradually add flour to make soft dough; turn on floured surface. Knead 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover.
Let rise to double in bulk.
Punch down.
Divide in half. Place in two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Cover.
Let rise again to double in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(You may brush the top with vegetable oil, when done baking, for a glossy look.)

title: lite fruit salad
directions: Mix together; chill.
Contains 15 calories per serving.

title: shrimp and corn soup
directions: In heavy pot, add oil and flour; cook until light brown.
Add onions and shrimp; saute lightly.
Add garlic and continue to stir.
Heat tomatoes separately.
Add tomatoes and cook slowly. (It will be like stew.)
Add parsley and broth.
Add corn and cook slowly for about 10 minutes.
Add seasoning to taste and add more broth if needed.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick.
Stir in coconut.
Put in baked pie shell.
Brown meringue.

title: garlicky brown sugar chicken
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken..
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix and place in bottom of a lightly buttered spring-pan.

title: fruity breakfast parfait
directions: You will need 4 stemmed sundae glasses.

title: broccoli-minute rice
directions: Pour hot water over broccoli.
Drain well.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: garlic-rosemary pork roast
directions: Untie roast and trim fat; re-tie roast.
Rub garlic over surface of roast.
Combine rosemary, chives and parsley.
Sprinkle evenly over roast.
Cover and chill 2 to 4 hours.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, milk, spices and sugar.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured).
Sprinkle dry cake mix over mixture in pan.
Melt the margarine and pour over the top of dry cake mix.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle walnuts over the cake.
Return to the oven and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add blueberry pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Put in fridge and let chill.

title: glazed franks
directions: Lightly brown the franks in small amount of oil on medium high.
Mix into the franks the currant jelly and mustard.
Cook over medium heat until glazed.

title: shaggy dogs candy
directions: In small saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate.
Stir in milk to make thin syrup.
Put coconut in shallow dish.

title: frosted banana bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; beat in eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Pour into a greased
15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until tests done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash in a small amount of water; drain and mix rest of ingredients.
Mix together 1/2 cup melted oleo with package of Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Line pan with dressing mix.
Bake at 350° until warm.

title: wedding punch
directions: Blend together 1/2 cup of granulated sugar with two tablespoons of unsulphured molasses.
The yield is equivalent to 1/2 cup brown sugar.

title: cheeseburger
directions: Cut apple, put applesauce on the apple.
That's how you make applesauce.

title: cabbage and beef casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add, heating thoroughly, but not browning, beef, salt and pepper.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix chicken and pimentos.
Brown celery, pepper and onion in oleo.
Combine with chicken mixture; mix well.
Cook rice in chicken broth until tender.
Place in layers in casserole dish the rice, mushroom soup and chicken mixture on top.
Bake 1 hour at 300° or until bubbly.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa together.
Add eggs; mix well. Stir in vanilla and milk.
Add melted margarine, then coconut and pecans.
Pour into two unbaked deep dish pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot tuna
directions: Combine oleo and flour in saucepan.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Add cheese, salt, pepper, Ro-Tel, tuna and onion.
Heat and stir until cheese melts.
Serve over toast, rice or chips. Good served with English peas.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Mix first five items together.
Cook until soft ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, butter and marshmallows.
Beat until very stiff.
Add nuts.
Pour in buttered dish and cut. Very good.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Boil chicken and save broth; debone.
Combine everything except cheese and chips and cook.
I usually cook mine 2 or 3 hours on low.
Fry chips and serve cheese on top.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook at 425° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into loaf.
Put in loaf pan which was sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Melt the brown sugar and butter.
Mix with the remaining ingredients and pour over cut up chicken.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: aunt ethel perdue's chicken salad
directions: Place egg yolks in top of double boiler. Whisk until smooth and light lemon color, then set aside.

title: tasty cheese ball
directions: Beat
cheese
and
butter with mixer until smooth.
Add mayonnaise,
beat
until fluffy.
Add chilies, pimentos, onion dip and
water.
Line quart dish with Saran Wrap and chill for 2 hours.
Can
make 1 large ball or 2 small ones.
Keeps for 3 weeks in fridge.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and lard to make crumbs.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa together.
Add sugar, salt, eggs, vanilla, flour and chopped nuts.
Pour into a greased 13X9 pan. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with marshmallow creme over top while hot.
Cover creme with icing.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Break raw veggies into small, individual florets and toss with dressing.
That's all!!
Can be "dressed up" with croutons, bacon bits, sunflower seeds or whatever.
Don't like Green Goddess dressing?
Try Ranch instead!

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450°, grease popover pan.
Beat eggs slightly with a fork, add milk, flour and salt.
Stir with a fork just until smooth.
Fill cups 1/2 full.
Bake 20 minutes, lower heat to 350° for 20 minutes until brown.
Remove at once.
Serve hot with butter.
Yields 10.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together until smooth the peanut butter and cream cheese.
Then add the 4x sugar until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and mix well.
Then spoon into crust.
Refrigerate a couple of hours.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: In small saucepan, combine mayonnaise, milk, salt and pepper until smooth.
Stirring constantly, cook over low heat for about 3 minutes, or just until heated.
Stir in lemon peel and lemon juice.
Serve with cooked asparagus, broccoli or other vegetables. Makes about 1 cup.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese and mayonnaise. Add other ingredients. Add shrimp. Serve chilled with chips.

title: grilled hot dogs
directions: Slit hot dogs lengthwise.
Fill with finely chopped onion.
Cut cheese in 1/4-inch strips and place on top of onions.
Wrap with a slice of bacon and pin with toothpick.
Place on shallow pan and put under broiler or place on outside grill.
Broil until bacon is crisp.

title: ding dong cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed. Bake in 2 round 9-inch cake pans. When cake is cool, place layers in freezer while preparing filling.

title: get 'em to eat spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan and place in oven to melt.
Remove pan from oven and set aside. Beat eggs, add flour, milk and baking powder; mix.
Add cheese and spinach, mixing well.
Spread into prepared pan and bake for 35 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes, cut into squares.
Yield:
24 (2 inch) squares.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two layer pans. Prepare and bake cake mix as directed on package.
When cooled, split each layer to make four layers.

title: jean's velveeta cheese loaves
directions: Cut up cheese in small pieces and let stand at room temperature until soft.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix well (will be sticky).
Refrigerate until firm.
Bring out and make 4 loaves.
Roll in ground walnuts and 1 teaspoon parsley.
Serve with favorite crackers.
Can be frozen individually until needed.

title: apple brown rice stuffing
directions: Cook apple, onion, celery, raisins, poultry seasoning, thyme and pepper in margarine in large skillet until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Use as stuffing for poultry pork roast.
To serve as a side dish, cook until thoroughly heated.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix flour, sugar and oatmeal.
Melt margarine; add to flour mixture, along with nuts.
Spread evenly on a cookie sheet; bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Crumble while hot; cool.
Put half of crumb mixture in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Drizzle with 6 ounces caramel ice cream topping.
Smooth 1/2 gallon softened vanilla ice cream over this.
Top
with remaining crumbs; drizzle with 6 more ounces caramel ice cream topping.
Freeze.
Do not use hot caramel topping.

title: cheese souffle(for that very important guest)
directions: Beat
eggs with dry
mustard,
milk,
sugar
and
salt. Layer bread (trim crusts)
and
cheese
alternately.
(I use a loaf pan.) Makes 2 or
layers.
Pour
milk,
eggs and other ingredients over layers.
Let stand 4 hours or overnight.
Put casserole in pan of water.
Bake
in
to 350° oven until puffed and brown (about 1
hour).
Goes with my sweet and sour chicken.
Serve with a
green
salad
and you have the perfect special meal for the special guests with "no sweat."

title: popovers
directions: Add milk to eggs, mix in dry ingredients, then add melted shortening and beat smooth.
Pour into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven down to 350°; finish baking for 25 minutes.
Poke each muffin with fork to let steam out.
Makes 6 Popovers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients.
Store in refrigerator and stir occasionally.
About 1 hour before serving, add sliced bananas (slice just before adding to mixture).
Serves 6 - 8.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in a large saucepan; bring to a boil. Take off burner and mix in peanut butter and Rice Krispies. Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch cake pan.
In small pan, melt chips on low heat. Spread as frosting onto Rice Krispie mixture.
Let cool, then eat.

title: sloppy ohs!
directions: Prepare biscuits as directed on package.
Meanwhile, in large skillet, brown ground beef, bell pepper and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Split biscuits; serve ground beef mixture over biscuits.
Makes 5 servings.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix cake mix from box directions; bake 15 minutes.
Mix 1 package vanilla pudding with 2 cups milk and 8 ounces cream cheese; beat until thick as pudding.
Spread on cooled cake. Spread drained pineapple over top.
Spread on container of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Store in refrigerator.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except oats and chocolate chips. When mixture is very smooth, add oats and mix well.
Add chocolate chips to mix.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.

title: chinese cashew chicken
directions: Mix all except nuts in a slow cooker.
Cook on low for 4 to 9 hours.
Stir in nuts and serve over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix all together.
Just before serving, add 2 to 3 bottles of 7-Up.

title: fruit danish delight
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Pile onto toast and broil until heated through and slightly browned on top.
Serves 1.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put in a large pan and cook on high the sugar, water, peanuts and Karo syrup.
Stir constantly for about 5 minutes or until you hear peanuts start to crack.
Take off heat.
Add vanilla flavoring, salt and baking soda.
Stir until foam leaves, then pour in a thin pan.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: In small bowl, beat the egg, cream cheese and 1/3 cup of sugar together.
Add the chocolate chips.
In large bowl, mix the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, water, oil, vinegar and vanilla. Fill foil cupcake cups 1/2 full with chocolate batter and drop 1 tablespoon of cream cheese mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: aunt dorothy's caramel icing
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar; bring to boil.
Stir constantly. Add milk; bring to boil again.
Stir constantly.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Gradually add powdered sugar.

title: carolina hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add water, evaporated milk, oil and egg.
Carefully drop batter by tablespoon into deep, hot oil (370°).
Cook a few at a time, turning once.
Fry until golden brown (3 to 5 minutes).
Drain well on paper towels.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cook beef and onions until meat turns grey.
Add other ingredients.
Cook on high temperature for 5 minutes, then simmer for 10 minutes.
Put in casserole dish.
Garnish with grated cheese and bake until cheese has melted at 350°.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery soup

title: impossible vegetable pie
directions: Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate.
Combine broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese.
Pour in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in a preheated 400° oven.
Serves 6.

title: party cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat sugar and margarine in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup candies. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Press 2 or 3 additional candies in each cookie.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add applesauce and soda.
Sift flour with seasonings and slowly add. Fold in raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Combine butter and cocoa in saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until butter melts.
Remove from heat, put in large mixing bowl. Add sugar and eggs.
Mix with electric mixer until blended. Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Stir in pecans. Put batter into lightly greased 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle marshmallows over the hot cake.
Immediately spread frosting over marshmallows.
Place on a rack to cool.
Cut into squares and serve.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Soak sliced cucumbers in 2 cups lime overnight.
Stir gently occasionally.
The following morning, rinse thoroughly three times, drain and pat dry.
Mix 2 quarts vinegar, 1/2 box spice, sugar and salt.
(I heat just enough to dissolve sugar.)
Put cucumbers in mixture and let stand 3 to 6 hours.
Bring mixture to a full boil and boil 30 to 35 minutes.
Put in sterile jars and seal.

title: almond crescent cookies
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Beat butter, sugar and almond extract.
Add flour and salt.
Stir in almonds, chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Roll dough by heaping teaspoonfuls. Shape into a crescent.
Place 2-inches apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Roll or shake on confectioners sugar.
Melt 3 squares of chocolate and 1 tablespoon butter.
Drizzle over cookies.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Add flour and sugar; mix well. Beat egg and add to flour mixture. Add vinegar and pineapple juice. Cook until thick.
Cool the mixture, Pour over the chopped apples. Add the pineapple and chopped nuts (reserve a few for the top). Mix in the LaCreme and sprinkle the remaining chopped nuts on the top.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed on box, or use one angel food cake. Crumble in large pieces; set aside.
Mix vanilla pudding as directed on package; set aside.
In saucepan, mix the sugar, cornstarch and 1 cup water; cook until thick.
Stir in the jello; cool.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts on stove.	Break chicken into chunks and lay in bottom of square Pyrex dish.
Stir together soup and sour cream and spoon over chicken.
Break up Ritz crackers into chunks over soup/sour cream mixture, then pour melted butter over this. Sprinkle with poppy seeds and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.	Serves 4.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Add egg yolks and beat thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Pour into greased pans (I use 3 round pans).
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients together to coat.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese pie
directions: Melt butter.
Crush crackers and make a crust in an 11 x 11-inch or oblong pan.

title: seafoam salad
directions: 1. Drain pears.
2. Heat 1 c. pear juice (if not enough add water).
3. Mix cream cheese with dry jello till it looks like green paste.
4. Add hot pear juice to jello mixture, mix well, then
cool and let thicken a bit.
5. Add mashed pears (mash with fork).
6. Fold in cool whip and nuts then cool.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine dry ingredients; add alternately to creamed mixture with milk and vanilla.

title: fruit cookie pizza
directions: Mix well together. Spread cream mixture on cookie.
Top with variety of fruit slices, strawberries, grapes, kiwi and banana.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Add dry ingredients to meat mixture; cool.
Chop cabbage.

title: christmas hot punch
directions: Put sugar, water, salt, cloves, cinnamon, allspice and cranberry juice together and bring to boil. Then add pineapple juice. Bring to boil again. Serve.

title: coconut cherry kiss cookies
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk and vanilla; beat well. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chopped cherries and 3 cups of the coconut. Cover tightly.
Chill 1 hour or until firm enough to handle.

title: apricot casserole
directions: Drain apricots well and place in dish (9 x 13-inches). Sprinkle brown sugar over apricots.
Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle over sugar.
Slice margarine over entire dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sandies
directions: Cream margarine.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Form small rolls 1 1/2-inches long or small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in slow oven (about 300°) for 20 minutes or until light brown.
While still hot, roll in powdered sugar twice.
Very good. Makes about 60.

title: orange bread
directions: Blend ingredients well.
Pour in greased bread pan.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.

title: barbecued beef chili
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients. Rub over brisket. Cut into 8 pieces. Place in a slow cooker. Combine the green pepper, onion, chili sauce, ketchup, barbecue sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Pour over meat. Cover and cook on high for 5 to 6 hours or until meat is tender. Remove meat. Cool slightly.

title: welsh rabbit
directions: Heat margarine in saucepan over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add beer gradually.
Stir in cheese.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Serve over toast.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: shrimp tempura
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg and add water.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
For the thin lacy batter, remove 1/2 cup batter. Add 2 tablespoons water.
The remaining portion is the thick dipping batter for shrimp.
Heat fat to 375°.
Dip fingers in the thin lacy batter and sprinkle over fat.

Repeat several times until a lacy network is formed. Dip shrimp in thick batter and place on lacy network when lightly browned. When tempura is golden brown, break network of batter and turn each shrimp.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Melt chips with milk over very low heat.
Mix in nuts.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until hardened.

title: aztec chili
directions: In skillet, brown beef in hot oil, chopping it into small granules as it cooks.
Drain off excess fat.
Sprinkle mix over meat; stir well.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil, stirring to blend flavors.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer at least 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: applesauce cake* * * * * * * *
directions: The following recipes are from Deborah Rehman, Medical Transcriptionist, Kaiser Permanente, Springfield.
Items not found in a regular grocery store can be found in specialty food stores featuring food items from India.

title: gooey butter coffee cake
directions: Blend cake mix with 2 eggs and melted butter; pour into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. In another bowl, combine cream cheese, remaining 2 eggs, vanilla and confectioners sugar minus 2 tablespoons. Mix well and spread over batter in dish. Bake in a 300° oven 15 minutes. Remove cake from oven and sprinkle the 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar on top. Return to oven and continue to bake 25 minutes longer. Do not overbake. Topping will not be gooey if cakes are baked too long.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix lemon juice with eagle brand milk until thick, fold in cool whip until blended. Divide between 2 pie crusts, chill 6 hours before serving. For richer color add 3 drops of yellow food coloring.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic in oil in deep heavy skillet or kettle.
When garlic is golden, add clam juice, basil, red pepper, oregano and parsley.
Simmer partially covered for 10 minutes.
Add clams and cook another 10 minutes.
Then add vermouth and cornstarch and cook 5 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Cook linguine according to package directions and serve clam sauce over it.
As an optional garnish, you may take 24 clams in shells, scrub them and put in pan with enough water to cover.
Set on high heat and as clams open up, remove them from water.
Serve them in shells on top of clam sauce.

title: last minute fudge
directions: Melt margarine and add peanut butter mix.
Add powdered sugar and mix well.
Pour into lightly greased pan.
Sets up in 1 hour.

title: grandma's jewels
directions: Combine flour, 1/3 cup brown sugar and butter.
Mix well, until it is like coarse crumbs.
Press into ungreased pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: grandma's chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender and then cut into bite sized pieces. Put chicken into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix soup, milk and sour cream. Spread over chicken. Top with crushed crackers.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out on rack and cool completely.
Spoon frosting over cake.

title: maine baked beans
directions: Soak the beans, covered with water, all night.
In the morning, put beans in saucepan; cover with cold water.
Heat until a white scum appears on the water.
Remove from stove; drain off water.

title: spicy pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until thick and foamy.

Stir in zucchini and pineapple. Combine all remaining ingredients. Stir gently into first mixture just until blended. Bake in 2 greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour. Cool on wire racks.

title: christmas cookies and icing
directions: Beat eggs. Add butter, sugar, milk and mix.
Mix soda and a little water (enough to stir) and add to mixture.
Sift flour and baking powder together and blend gradually into cookie mixture. Grease and flour cookie sheets.
Roll dough into 1/4 inch thickness and cut with Christmas cookie cutters and place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10-12 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw bread loaves as directed on package.
Roll out dough on floured surface into a rectangle.
Sprinkle with
oil.
Sprinkle with fresh Parmesan cheese, garlic salt and oregano.
Layer in middle of the dough salami, Provolone cheese, bell pepper, cooked ham and tomato.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Fold each half of dough over to center and seal. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and oregano over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: lentil roast
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 2 medium sprayed casserole dishes and bake until firm at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with gravy or slice for sandwiches.
Serves 12.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Dissolve all liquids; peel carrots and cut 1 1/2-inch length and then in half and cook.
Layer carrots, bell pepper and onion in bowl.
Pour hot liquid over and cover; put in refrigerator overnight.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cover raisins with water.
Boil until plump; drain.
Add butter, sugar, whipped egg whites, egg yolks, vanilla and vinegar. Stir until well mixed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cover with pie shell and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: steak sauce marinade
directions: Mix altogether.
Soak round steak in marinade at least 1 hour; grill.
Can use chicken breasts instead of steak.
After using marinade, throw excess out.
Do not save to reuse.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. Melt butter and blend in flour.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add salt, pepper, onion and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate brownie cake
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Mix the flour, sugar and cocoa. Add to the boiling mixture. Add the eggs, buttermilk and soda. Add the first mixture to this.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in greased and floured pan (large 1-inch deep cookie sheet is best).
Top hot cake with icing.

title: gnocci
directions: Clean and peel potatoes.
Boil until soft.
Mash.
To the warm mashed potato, add egg, salt and enough of the flour to make dough.
Knead dough until smooth.
Roll into pieces 3/4-inch thick and 1 1/2 inches long.
Drop into boiling water and boil until dumpling rises to the top.
Drain.
Serve with butter and Parmesan cheese.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk. Add pumpkin, spice mix and 2 cups Cool Whip. Put in graham cracker crusts and top with remaining Cool Whip. This makes 2 pies. Place in the refrigerator and chill.

title: peggy's meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except grape jelly and chili sauce.
Roll into balls and deep fry.
Drain balls of grease.
Melt jelly and chili sauce together.
Put balls in sauce mixture and simmer.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes and
salt and pepper.
Dip into milk and then flour.
Mix corn meal and green pepper together, then dip floured tomato in corn meal mixture.
Fry in iron skillet in hot grease.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix horseradish and dry mustard well.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Will keep in refrigerator for years.
Good with ham, pork, turkey, etc.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with shrimp, crab, oysters, crawfish or fish.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix all except soda water.
Pour into freezer.
Finish filling freezer with soda water.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Cut water chestnuts in two.
Cut bacon (uncooked)
in strips of halves, wrap around chestnuts and secure with toothpicks (white).

title: dutch butter cake
directions: Blend thoroughly all ingredients in a Cuisinart.
Pour into pie plate for baking.
Coat all dough surfaces with reserved egg white.
Bake in 375° oven for approximately 1/2 hour.
Check carefully that it does not burn.
Serve at room temperature.

title: egg, sausage and potato casserole
directions: Fry potatoes and onion in butter until browned.
Place in greased 8-inch glass baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Crumble sausage and spread over cheese.
(Top with drained mushrooms, if desired.)
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Serves 6.

title: corn bread meat loaf
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions, garlic, celery and bell peppers.
Add the soup; let cook about 10 minutes.
Drain off excess fat from skillet.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Make corn bread according to directions on box; pour over ground meat mixture.
Bake in a hot oven until corn bread is golden brown.

title: easy lemon meringue pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in milk, lemon juice and rind.
Pour into pie crust.
In small bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy; gradually add sugar while beating until whites are stiff but not dry.
Spread meringue on top of pie, sealing edges.
Bake for 15 minutes in a preheated oven at 350°.
Chill before serving.

title: oysters rockefeller
directions: In small saucepan, saute celery, onions, garlic and parsley in margarine until tender.
In blender, combine sauteed vegetables, spinach and salt.
Blend until almost pureed.
When necessary, stop blender and push vegetables into blades.
Fill a shallow, ovenproof serving dish with rock salt.
Nest oyster shells into salt bed.
(The rock salt holds shells in place and keeps oysters hot.)
Place the oysters in the shells.
Top each oyster with spinach mixture.
Combine bread crumbs and melted margarine; sprinkle crumb mixture over oysters.
Dust with paprika.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 appetizer servings of 3 oysters each.

title: broccoli-bacon-raisin salad
directions: Fry bacon to crisp, drain and chop finely.
Add to vegetables and raisins.
Set aside.
While making dressing, blend mayo, vinegar and sugar.
Mix into vegetable mixture.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: crescent roll lasagna
directions: Mix beef and sauce.
Set aside.
Mix parmesan, cottage cheese, and egg.
Set aside.
Pour beef mixture into a well greased rectangle baking dish.
Top with the two mozzarella cheese slices.
Unroll one can of crescents into rectangles on top of each mozzarella cheese slice.
Top this layer of crescents with the cheese and egg mixture.
unroll remaining can of crescents into rectangles on top of cheese mixture.
Bake at 375 degrees for 25 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream the cheese, pie crusts and Tabasco sauce until well mixed.
Push through cookie press or roll into tiny balls.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned.
Remove, cool and store.

title: black pepper cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add oil, wine or water and the salt water.
Take small amount of dough, pat into finger shape and knot both ends together.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 minutes or until lightly browned in a 400° oven.

title: eve's chocolate dream cake("quick 'n easy")
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Let cool.

title: italian supper soup
directions: Brown sausage pieces in a large soup kettle over medium heat. Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender, but not brown. Add mushrooms. Cook 5 more minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients except macaroni. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Uncover and bring to a boil. Gradually stir in macaroni and cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Stir frequently. Serve hot.

title: banana shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or electric mixer bowl. Beat until smooth and creamy.

title: meat loaf-stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
Immerse in boiling water for 3 minutes; drain.
Pour 1 cup spaghetti sauce into the bottom of a shallow baking dish.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, combine meat loaf, rice, onion, chopped green pepper and remaining spaghetti sauce.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat for 5 to 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: pecan praline pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix eggs, corn syrup, brown sugar, salt, butter and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle pecan halves evenly over filling.
Push down with fork to coat with filling.
Place pie on lower shelf of oven and bake 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 15 minutes more.
If pie is not done yet, leave in another 10 minutes until set.

title: lobster thermidor
directions: Make white sauce by sauteing onion and mushrooms in butter until transparent.
Add flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Add, slowly stirring until thickened, chicken broth and milk.
Stir in the egg yolk and cooked lobster.
Pour into 4 lobster tail shells, 4 scallop shells or a casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs flavored with 2 tablespoons Parmesan or 1/8 teaspoon oregano or 1/8 teaspoon sage.
Bake at 350° until bread crumbs are brown, just a few minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers across top and scoop out insides.
Bring 4 quarts water to boil.
Put clean peppers in and blanche for 3 minutes. In frypan, cook chop meat, garlic, onion and nutmeg.
Drain and add rice.
Spoon into pepper.
Place in roasting pan.
Pour tomatoes over and place in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes. Serves 4.

title: apple muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and cloves.
Add apples and walnuts.
In small bowl, beat eggs with fork.
Beat in buttermilk and butter.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Fill muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: hot potato salad - the hofbran haus way
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.	Remove from pan; drain and crumble. Saute onions in bacon fat until glossy (do not brown).
Turn off heat.
Stir in flour, then heat until light yellow.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Add sugar, salt and spices.
Cook until mixture is of medium thickness.
Add potatoes, crumbled bacon and parsley.
Mix carefully to prevent mashing potatoes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts in top of a double boiler. Place over hot boiling water and stir until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Spread into pan and let cool.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Combine soup and beans in casserole dish.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and mix until well blended.

title: texas cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix first 6 ingredients.
Set aside. In a medium saucepan, bring to a boil, oleo, cocoa and water. Stir into flour mixture and beat well.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: banana nog
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender.
Whiz about 30 seconds or until blended.
Pour into chilled glasses.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 2 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken
and
margarine
with salt and pepper, then debone chicken, saving
broth.
Add
cream of chicken, cream of mushroom and chicken
broth
to
rice and deboned chicken.
Mix well.
Bake in casserole dish at 250° until slightly brown.

title: pea and lettuce salad
directions: Combine lettuce, peas, carrot
and red onion in a salad bowl. In a separate bowl, mix mayonnaise, no-oil dressing and pepper. Add liquid mixture
to
ingredients in salad bowl and toss. Serves 2.

title: crabbies
directions: Spread mixture on quartered English muffins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until browned.
May be baked fresh or frozen.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion in skillet.
Add and simmer 2 minutes: catsup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Place in casserole dish: green beans, then barbecue mix.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy dinner rolls
directions: Heat milk to hot.
Stir in sugar, shortening and salt.
When cool, stir in yeast and beat well, then beat in eggs and flour. Let rise and work out.
Don't overbake.

title: white wine cake
directions: Mix together in mixer.
Line pan with nuts and pour batter over them.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: never fail popovers
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into 5 custard cups which have been sprayed with Pam.
Set in cold oven and turn to 450° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave fillet of sole in lemon parsley butter
directions: Place margarine in rectangular baking dish, 12 x 8-inch or 10-inch casserole.
Microwave at High until melted.
Blend in remaining ingredients except fish fillets.
Coat both sides of fish with butter sauce.
Arrange in baking dish.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave at High until fish flakes easily in center with fork, 5 to 6 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat eggplant slices.
Cook coated eggplant in a large skillet in hot oil until golden brown and barely tender (approximately 5 minutes).
Drain on paper towels.
Spoon a thin layer of sauce over the bottom of a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Line with a layer of eggplant.
Sprinkle with cheese (use more if desired to suit flavor).
Pour part of the beaten eggs on top.
Repeat layers ending with sauce and beaten egg.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: butter pecan pie crust
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: fudge
directions: Cook 4 minutes after it starts to boil.
Add peanut butter and Marshmallow.
Beat thoroughly, pour into greased pan.

title: acorn squash souffle
directions: Rinse and peel squash; cut in half and remove seeds.
Cut into cubes and boil until tender (like potatoes).
When done, mash the squash in a large bowl or pot.
Whip with beater until smooth (this will also remove any stringy pieces).
When smooth, add all other ingredients and beat to combine.
Pour into a long baking dish and bake at 350° until firm and brown around edges.
Serve hot or cold. Happy baking.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Presoak peas. Drain. In large pot, place peas and remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until tender (1 1/2 to 2 hours).

title: meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch and cold water together.
Add to boiling water and cook until clear, stirring constantly.
Set aside to cool. Beat together egg whites, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat until stiff, then add cornstarch mixture and beat again.

title: honey mustard chicken
