directions: Combine mustard and honey in a small bowl. Add dill, orange peel and marmalade. Place chicken skin side down in baking pan. Brush sauce on top of chicken.
Turn chicken over. Pull back skin and brush meat with sauce. Pull skin back over chicken and brush with remaining sauce. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until juices run clear.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook pasta as directed and drain. Brown beef; drain. Add tomato sauce, water, taco seasoning and salsa to beef. Let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from heat; add pasta and mix well. Pour into casserole dish; top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour over meat.
Refrigerate overnight or let stand at least 2 hours.
Turn meat occasionally and baste.
Serve with rice.

title: mother-in-law's cranberry jelly
directions: Put cranberries in covered saucepan.
Bring to boil and cook until most all of the cranberries have "popped".
Strain and mix in 2 cups sugar.
Cool.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all Jell-O plus water together, then add other ingredients.
Chill well.
Yields 60 cups.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Spray an 11 x 15-inch cake pan with Pam.
Lay whole graham crackers on bottom.
Mix pudding and milk together and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour half of this mixture over graham crackers in pan. Place another layer of graham crackers on top of pudding.
Place remaining pudding mixture over second layer of graham crackers, then place a third layer of graham crackers on top.

title: apple upside down cake
directions: In a 9 x 9 pan, melt butter and spread evenly over bottom of pan. Spread 1/2 cup brown sugar evenly over butter.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Arrange apple slices over pecans.
Sprinkle apples with lemon juice.
Set aside.
Cream together butter, sugar and remaining 2/3 cup brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift together all remaining dry ingredients and stir into butter mixture.
Mix in buttermilk.
Spread batter over apple slices, being careful not to displace apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving platter.
Slice into squares and garnish with whipped cream.
Serve warm.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Mix all; put into spring pan. Do not pack. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Cool crust before adding filling.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and let stand 20 minutes.
Then add shortening, white sugar, brown sugar and eggs to oatmeal mixture. Mix all ingredients together and bake in a moderate oven, until done; use a toothpick to check if done.

title: butterscotch fingers
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar and blend.
Add egg and vanilla, then beat.
Add flour and baking powder; beat.
Mixture will be stiff.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 48 bars.

title: harvest casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, tomatoes and seasonings.
Pat into a layer about 1-inch thick in a baking pan or dish.
Add rest of ingredients in layers, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angel's delight
directions: Prepare whipped topping according to package.
Set side.
Tear cake into bite-size pieces.
In large mixing bowl beat cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Fold in whipped topping.
Add cake pieces and stir gently to coat evenly.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with pie filling and chill.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix zucchini, onion, cheese, Bisquick and seasonings in large bowl.
Pour in large well-greased casserole dish.
Beat eggs and oil together; pour over zucchini mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
This dish freezes well, just reheat.

title: beer bread
directions: Toast bread until lightly browned on both sides under a broiler.
Rub top of bread with garlic.
Return slices to broiling tray.
Sprinkle olive oil over bread slices.
Top with tomato slices and pepper.
Broil close to flame for 1 minute and serve at once.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix dry ingredients together and set aside.
Cream sugars and butter.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Top with candy kiss and bake an additional 2 minutes.

title: "strawberry fluff"
directions: Pour boiling water over Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in frozen berries.
Stir in ice cream until well mixed.
Pour in glasses.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.

title: deluxe old fashioned fruit cake
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Grease 2 loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inches) or a 10-inch tube pan.
Measure all ingredients except fruit and nuts. Blend on low speed for about 1/2 minute, then stir in fruit and nuts.
Put aluminum foil over cake the last hour of baking time so it won't burn or get too brown.
Bake 2 1/2 or 3 hours or until toothpick is clean when tested.

title: blueberry crunch cake
directions: Pour pineapple in long pan; cover pineapple with blueberries. Sprinkle 1/2 cup of sugar on top of blueberries; mix and pour yellow cake mix on top of blueberries. Cut up margarine and dot top of cake mix. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup of sugar on top. Add chopped nuts and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fudge squares
directions: Melt chocolate and butter; cool.
Gradually add eggs, salt and sugar; beat until light and creamy.
Fold in melted chocolate. Add vanilla, flour and walnuts.
Mix until smooth.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with waxed or parchment paper.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon hard candy
directions: Cook the sugar, water and corn syrup until hard ball stage. Take off stove.
Add the food coloring and cinnamon oil.
Stir; pour in cookie sheet.
Let harden and crack it.
Put pieces in a bag; put in a little powdered sugar to keep it from getting sticky.

title: tomato and broccoli bake
directions: Thaw broccoli if frozen.
In a large kettle or Dutch oven, cook pasta, uncovered, in boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes, or until tender; drain.
Set aside.
In a 3-quart saucepan, cook onion and garlic in hot margarine.
Add fresh broccoli (add frozen later), tomatoes, parsley, bouillon granules, salt, oregano and basil.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 3 minutes. Stir in pasta and 1/2 cup of cheese.
(Add thawed broccoli.) Transfer to an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake, uncovered, 5 more minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroni beef saute
directions: Saute beef, macaroni, onion, bell pepper and garlic in hot oil until macaroni turns slightly yellow; drain off excess fat.
Add tomato juice and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Uncover and simmer for several more minutes or until sauce is reduced in consistency.
Serves 4.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil.
Add flour and mix until it forms a ball.
COOL!!
Add eggs one at a time, beat.

title: mexicana rice
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in margarine.
Remove from heat; combine with remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Toss lightly to mix and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Garnish with paprika.
One cup chopped ham can be added to make a main dish.

title: cheesy artichoke heart appetizers
directions: Unroll dough into rectangles.
Press onto bottom and sides of 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan to form crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Crumble Doritos; put layer on bottom of large baking dish.
Spoon in ground beef mixture.
Add Doritos on top.
Put shredded cheese on top about 10 minutes before done.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.

title: new orleans pralines
directions: Cook syrup with candy thermometer to 236°.
Remove and add pecans and vanilla.
Let cool until you can touch bottom of pan. Beat until thick and drop on cookie sheet covered with wax paper.

title: bethany salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling.
Add gelatin and stir to dissolve. Chill until partially set.
Soften cream cheese.
Add to gelatin mixture and blend.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold; chill until set.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Mix and sift flour and salt.
Add alternately with grated apples to egg mixture.
Stir in lemon peel and pecans.
Batter will be stiff.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan, 8 x 5 x 3-inch at 350°
for 50 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: hush puppies
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, then other ingredients and mix well. Drop in hot fat where fish was cooked.
Cook until golden brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine bananas, eggs, sugar, salt, soda, flour and nuts. Grease loaf pan and line with wax paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Remove wax paper immediately when bread is done baking.

title: rolled dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening using pastry blender or fork. Make a well in center.
Add egg and small amount of cold water to make soft dough.
Roll on well floured surface (1/3 of dough at a time) to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in strips and crosswise (about 2-inch squares).
Drop into boiling broth.
Cover, turn heat to low.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: family christmas fillet
directions: Cut meat in 2 pound chunks.
Melt butter in large roasting pan.
Chop onions and saute in butter until onions are tender. Slice mushrooms in half or quarters.
Add to onion/butter mixture and coat.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix with hands.
Put in pan; spread out.
Put paprika and parsley flakes on top.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash in large mixing bowl.
Add rest of ingredients, except cheese.
Put in greased casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: martha howard's popcorn balls
directions: Cook the sugar, cream and Karo to a soft ball stage.
Add coconut flavoring and flake coconut.
Pour immediately over a dishpan size bowl full of popped corn.
Stir and form into balls. If your hands become sticky, just put them into a little cold water.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Bring green pepper, hot peppers, sugar and vinegar to a rolling boil.
Boil hard for one minute.
Remove from heat, stir in about 4 or 5 drops green food coloring.
Add certo.
Let stand 5 minutes. Skim off foam.
Put in small jars and seal.
Great on crackers with cream cheese.

title: green chili chicken
directions: Preheat Oven to: 350°.
Stir Rotel tomatoes and soup in sauce pan and cook 6 - 8 minutes.
Stir in chicken and onions.
Put 2 tortillas in 9 X 13 pan.
Spread 1/3 meat, cilantro, tomato and soup mix.
Keep layering and top with cheese.
Cooking Time: 30 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients together, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix together, then add nuts if so desired.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken with rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion in butter until light brown. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: picante black bean soup(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Cook bacon over medium-high heat in large saucepan until crisp. Remove to paper towels.
Set aside. Add onion and garlic to drippings; cook and stir 3 minutes. Add beans, broth, water, 3/4 cup picante sauce, salt and oregano.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Ladle into soup bowls; dollop with sour cream. Sprinkle with reserved bacon. Serve with additional picante sauce and crackers.

title: pan roasted baby carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place carrots in a shallow baking dish and sprinkle the basil over them.
Pour chicken stock over carrots and dot them with butter.
Cover the casserole loosely and roast for 45 minutes or until carrots are very tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tootie bread
directions: Slice bread and place Swiss (or your favorite cheese) between slices.
Mix softened butter, mustard, onion flakes and poppy seed.
Spread on top of loaf (like frosting).
Crumble bacon on top.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: taco salad dip
directions: In blender, mix cream cheese with sour cream.
Add dash of milk.
Add taco seasoning package.
Mix well.
Pour onto large round plate with a lip on it.
Cut up lettuce in small pieces. Place on taco mixture.
Cut up tomatoes and put on top of lettuce. Follow with the onion.
Slice the black olives and green olives; spread over mixture.
Cover with grated cheese.
Use tortilla chips to scoop it out with.

title: best ever pumpkin pie
directions: Melt the margarine in a saucepan.
Add the pumpkin, salt, syrup, spices and sugars.
Cook for about 10 minutes, stirring. Then stir in egg yolks.
Cook for about 15 minutes longer, stirring frequently.
Add pecans, raisins and cherries and place in pie crust.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes.

title: chicken-rice soup
directions: Combine chicken and water in a Dutch oven; bring to boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken, reserving broth.
Let chicken cool.
Skin, bone and dice chicken; set aside.

title: quick rice pudding
directions: Place pudding mix in a large bowl; gradually blend in milk. Stir in rice, raisins and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg.
Microwave at High for approximately 8 minutes, or until mixture thickens, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Stir again.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Chill.

title: shortbread wedges
directions: Mix butter and powdered sugar in a large bowl until smooth and creamy.
Add flour.
Stir until well mixed.
Spread dough evenly in an ungreased pie pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef; mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: layered pea salad
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and mash when done.
Add remaining ingredients. Set aside.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Wrap each apple slice in one of the thinly rolled biscuit halves.
Place in a baking dish.
Pour the sauce over the dumplings.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 375° preheated oven.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix strawberries, sugar, egg whites and lemon juice for 15 minutes in large bowl. Then fold in whipping cream.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter or margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low until cheese is thoroughly melted.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until soft.
Add coloring and flavoring.
Gradually add confectioners sugar, mixing and kneading until consistency is like pie dough or putty.
Add more sugar if you want firmer.
Roll into balls the size of a marble. Place one side in small amount of granulated sugar.
Place sugar side down into cavity of mold, pressing from edge to center. Unmold at once and place on waxed paper to dry.
Makes 20 to 25 mints.

title: butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine margarine, 1 egg and cake mix and press into 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Combine 2 eggs, cream cheese and confectioners sugar until creamy, then pour over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Completely cool before cutting into squares.

title: mother's fruit cake
directions: Cover nuts and fruit with flour.

title: bean dips
directions: Place all ingredients into food processor or blender. Mix/blend well.
Serve with corn chips, tortillas or pita bread.

title: french onion steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Trim off excess fat and pound flour into both sides of each piece.
Brown each piece in hot oil. In Dutch oven, add steak, soup mix (undiluted), hot water and seasonings.
Cover and simmer slowly until fork-tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Thicken gravy with cornstarch.
For darker gravy, use Kitchen Bouquet.
Great served with creamed potatoes.

title: crabmeat delight
directions: Whip cheese until smooth.
Add Worcestershire, lime juice and mayo.
Place lettuce on tray.
Pile cheese in mound or spread 1 1/2 inches.
Scatter crabmeat on cheese; drizzle with chili sauce. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat broccoli to thaw.
Drain.
In large bowl, mix together broccoli, eggs, soup, onion and mayonnaise.
In separate bowl, mix crackers and cheese.
Mix 1/2 cheese mixture with broccoli. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining cheese and crackers with margarine.
Sprinkle over broccoli mixture. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: fresh toasted bread crumbs
directions: Heat butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add bread crumbs; cook, tossing to coat with butter about 10 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: king ranch chicken no. 1
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Combine chicken, onion and green pepper.
Place 4 tortillas, which have been dipped in chicken broth, in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with chicken mixture.
Combine seasonings, soups and tomatoes and pour over chicken mixture.
Top with 6 tortillas.
Spread grated cheese on top of tortillas.
Pour chicken broth on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: spinach noodle kugel
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Cook and drain noodles. Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until brown.

title: deluxe fried chicken
directions: Cut up and skin fryer.
Rinse with cold water; drain and cover with buttermilk.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and chill overnight.
Salt and pepper each piece and thoroughly dredge in flour.
Cook in iron skillet in hot canola oil at below medium to medium heat.
Cover and turn as needed.
Chicken will have a very brown crust and taste very juicy, sweet and tender.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Heat syrup or fruit juice.
Combine egg yolks, sugar and salt. Add syrup or juice slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook over hot water until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice slowly.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Combine all the ingredients except the eggplant, olive oil and 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Wash eggplants; cut off top green stem and slice carefully lengthwise (approximately 6 to 7 slices) to form a fan, do not completely cut through to the base.
Line a pan with foil; place eggplant in the pan.
Take a portion of the filling and place between the layers.
Coat heavy with olive oil.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
After 45 minutes check for tenderness and if eggplant is tender, uncover and sprinkle with half cup cheese and bake another 10 to 15 minutes.
Transfer to serving plate with large spatula.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt butter and sugar together over low heat.
Remove from heat and mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased 11 X 14 pan at 375 for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broiled fluff frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients; spread over the top of hot cake. Broil slowly, about 2 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes enough to frost one 9-inch square pan.

title: silly brownies
directions: Melt chocolate	chips
in
a
large
saucepan.	Add the nuts, condensed milk, flour, margarine and vanilla.
Mix well. Remove from heat
and
drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake 6 minutes at 350°.

title: garbage dip
directions: Chop up tomatoes and green onions.
Add olives, chilies, tomatoes and green onions to mix ingredients of oil, garlic salt and vinegar.
Mix well.
Let set overnight or for several hours in refrigerator.
Good with corn chips and wheat crackers.

title: jello squares
directions: Mix jello and gelatine together.
Add boiling water; dissolve the jello and gelatine.
Stir in heavy cream.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let set in refrigerator at least 1/2 hour.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Bring oleo and water to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour and eggs (one at a time), beating after each one.
Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown and season ground beef.
Press rolls in bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Beat egg and glaze rolls.
Mix beef, Hunt's sauce and beans.
Layer mixture and cheese.
Two layers of each should be enough.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients (cake mix, oleo and egg).
Pour (pat) into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan (like pie crust).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Pour over baked cake.
Sprinkle with 1 to 1 1/2 cups pecans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
When cool, cut in bars.
Better if served the next day.

title: cherry strawberry slush
directions: Put bananas in blender with small amount of the liquid and blend.
Put strawberries in blender and blend.
Mix all ingredients and put in freezer.
Thaw until slushy to serve. Delicious!
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil or pressure cook hen until thoroughly cooked.
Debone and reserve stock.
Saute onions, bell peppers, garlic and celery in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and 1 quart chicken stock. Add Tony's Creole Seasoning and poultry seasoning.
Allow to cook slowly for 3 hours adding stock if necessary.
Add 1/2 cup cheese during last half hour of cooking together with mushrooms and cooked chicken.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.
Offer additional cheese when serving (Italian style grated natural cheeses).

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix well beaten eggs, flour, sugar, canned milk and vanilla. Add pudding mix and stir.
Pour in freezer container and fill to "fill line" with whole milk.
Freeze with ice and rock salt.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt together in double boiler or microwave.
Serve with Doritos or Fritos.

title: indian corn casserole
directions: Combine green chilies, cream cheese, margarine and milk together.
Heat on low until smooth.
Drain corn and add to this mixture.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° until hot.

title: quick upside-down cake
directions: Grease sides of an an 8-inch cast-iron skillet.
Melt butter in skillet; sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut 3 pineapple slices in half; arrange whole slices in center of brown sugar mixture and place half slices around it.
Arrange pecans and cherries over the top.
Set skillet aside.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions and stir in vanilla.
Spoon batter into skillet over pineapple slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Immediately invert cake onto serving plate.

title: microwave english muffin pizza
directions: Spread each muffin half with 1 tablespoon sauce.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon cheese.
Top with any garnish you like.
Arrange in a circular pattern on a microwave-safe plate lined with paper towels.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 1 1/2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Rotate once during cooking.
Makes 4 pizzas.

title: confetti cornbread
directions: Heat oil in an 8-inch cast-iron skillet or 8-inch square pan in a 400° oven for 5 minutes.
Combine cornmeal and next 8 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture. Set aside.
Combine yogurt, egg and pimiento.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Remove skillet from oven.
Pour oil into batter, stirring until blended.
Pour mixture into hot skillet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Serve immediately.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook over low heat until thick. Let cool.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Gently fold in 1 cup cream, whipped.
Spoon into greased 8-inch square pan.
Freeze.
Cut into squares.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: frozen cream-style corn
directions: Combine all and cook until it boils well, stirring often. Cool, box and freeze.
When ready to use, thaw in double boiler and heat until hot.
Ready to eat!

title: baked corn
directions: Mix corn, eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder and salt together. Gradually add milk and mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish. Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, 40 minutes at 350°.

title: curried chicken
directions: Made best and easiest in an electric skillet.
Melt oleo, add onion, cook until tender.
Add flour, mixing well.
Stir in seasonings.
Slowly add stock, stirring to blend without lumps. Add half and half and chicken.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: jello surprise
directions: Combine water, jello and strawberries.
Chill until soft. Combine butter, 3 1/2 tablespoons sugar and crushed pretzels.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 7 1/2 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: layered salad
directions: In a bowl layer:
1/2 head lettuce (in pieces), 1/2 lb.

diced bacon, chopped hard-boiled eggs, salt and pepper to taste, chopped onion, uncooked peas, cauliflower and 1/2 head lettuce for cover. Frost with mixture of 1 cup Miracle Whip and 1 cup Hellmann's mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Cover and refrigerate for 6 to 8 hours.

title: round sauerbraten
directions: Cut meat in 1-inch squares.
In large frypan, brown meat on all sides in oil.
Remove meat from pan; add gravy mix and water. Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining ingredients except noodles.
Return meat to pan; cover and simmer until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.

title: cranberry scones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a large baking sheet.
Stir together flour, sugar and orange peel in mixing bowl. Cut butter into flour mixture with pastry blender or two knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in cranberries.
Break egg into measuring cup.
Add enough milk to make 2/3 cup.
Add milk mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir gently with a fork until dry particles begin to cling together.
Do not add more liquid.
Mixture may be crumbly.
Turn mixture out onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth and gently push particles together to form a ball of dough. Divide dough in half.

Place both halves on prepared baking sheet and press each into a 6-inch circle. Cut each circle into 8 wedges using floured sharp knife or pizza cutter. Separate wedges slightly, leaving about 1/2-inch between each wedge.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 5 minutes on baking sheet and carefully slide rings off baking sheet.

title: mashed potato doughnuts
directions: Blend Crisco, egg and milk.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Combine two mixtures with mashed potatoes and mix thoroughly. Roll on lightly floured pastry cloth or board and cut with floured doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep Crisco heated to 365° 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Dip in powdered sugar.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl and serve.

title: apple bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat in sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Stir in apple.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swiss-spinach quiche
directions: Separate biscuit dough and spread into ungreased 9-inch pie pan or 9-inch quiche pan, pressing together to form crust.
Toss cheese with flour.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christine's pralines
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Heat on medium to high heat, stirring occasionally while frothy.
When consistency is like syrup, add 3 cups pecans.
Stir until all are well coated. If extra liquid is in pan, stir in more nuts until syrup is all used.
Spread on wax paper or cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Let cool and enjoy.

title: turkey salad
directions: Combine tomatoes, broccoli, spinach, turkey, eggs and green onion in a large bowl.
Combine Italian dressing and mustard, stirring until blended.
Pour over salad and toss to blend.
Serve immediately.

title: cheddar apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter or line with paper baking cups, 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until blended.
Stir in yogurt and sugar.
Add baking mix; stir until just moistened.
Stir in cheese and raisins.
Fill prepared muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, about 15 minutes.
Remove muffins from pan.
Serve warm or place on wire racks to cool completely.
Store in a closed plastic container.
Makes 12.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter, then add salt, well beaten eggs and mashed bananas.
Add flour and soda (sifted three times) and nuts. Bake 15 minutes in loaf at 300°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden brown. Add soup and cheese; blend together. Add rice and broccoli.
Pour into buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until firm.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Arrange half of asparagus in lightly greased 21 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine next 6 ingredients.
Stir gently and spoon 1/2 of mixture over asparagus.
Repeat layers.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: maple-nut ice cream
directions: In a large bowl combine milk and pudding mix.
Beat 2 minutes until well blended.
Refrigerate about 5 minutes.
Add sugar, half and half, maple flavoring and eggs to pudding mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into freezer can.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 3 quarts or 24 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: champagne punch
directions: Blend and chill all ingredients except champagne.
To serve pour in punch bowl and add champagne.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Melt butter in stock pot.
Lightly saute vegetables.
Add remaining ingredients and 1 1/2 quarts of water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, partially covered, stirring occasionally, for 1 1/2 hours. Season with salt and pepper. Serve with warm noodles or rice.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix food coloring and cocoa. Add to creamed mixture.
Add salt and vanilla and buttermilk.
Add flour a little at a time, beating well after each mixture.
Mix baking soda and vinegar.
Do not beat after adding baking soda and vinegar.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Break egg in a measuring cup. (Beat lightly.) Add milk to make 1/2 cup. Add to other ingredients. Makes 3 shells.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: low-fat strawberry heaven
directions: Cut cake horizontally into 3 layers.
Place 1 layer on dish. Stir crushed strawberries and milk into 1 cup of the whipped topping in a large bowl.
Spread 1/2 of the strawberry mixture on cake layer.
Repeat layers, ending with cake.
Frost top and sides of cake with remaining whipped topping.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: sausage cake(permanent mold casting)
directions: Cover raisins with water and boil 20 minutes.
While raisins are boiling, mix sausage, cinnamon and sugar together.
With slotted spoon, put raisins in sausage mixture (save raisin water). Measure 1 cup raisin juice (if not a cup, add water).
Add baking soda to juice, then to sausage mixture.
Juice will foam when soda is added.
Add flour and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 400° for 55 minutes or until toothpick is clean.

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 2 long rectangles. Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan; press over bottom to form crust.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and almond extract; blend until smooth.
Spread over crust.
Spoon pie filling over cream cheese mixture.
Combine flour, brown sugar and margarine; mix until crumbly.
Stir in almonds; sprinkle crumb mixture over pie filling.
Return to oven and bake an additional 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely; cut into squares.
If desired, serve with whipped cream and garnish with almonds and mint.

title: creamy green salsa
directions: Combine all the above ingredients. Chill.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: allege
directions: Mix crushed pineapple with pudding.
Add Cool Whip, fruit cocktail and Mandarin oranges.
Let cool in refrigerator until thick (about 1 hour).

title: cherry punch bowl cake
directions: Drain maraschino cherries and pineapple and set aside. Bake 3 layers of yellow cake mix by package directions. In bottom of large glass punch bowl, break up one layer of cake. Next, add a thin layer of pineapple and then one of cherry pie filling. Next, a layer of pudding, mixed by package directions, a layer of whipped topping a layer of pecans and a layer of coconut. Top entire dessert with the chopped maraschino cherries. Repeat the same layering process three times before the final topping is added. Chill for 2 hours before serving. Will serve a large crowd. Recipe may be used in smaller amounts in order to fit punch bowl that is available.

title: raisin pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in baking dish.

title: macaroni-shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Add peas/carrots and shrimp.
Mix other ingredients and then add to macaroni.
Chill.

title: carrot pudding
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger.
Stir gently with a whisk.
In a medium bowl, combine melted butter, grated carrots, grated apple, brown sugar, raisins and eggs and stir until the sugar is dissolved.
Stir into flour mixture.

title: georgia pea-picking cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding eggs one at a time.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 8 or 9-inch cake pans at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crispix mix
directions: Heat and boil the brown sugar and butter for 1 minute.
Pour over Crispix cereal and pecans.
Bake in 300° oven for 10 minutes; stir, bake 10 minutes, then stir again and then bake a final 8 minutes.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into small pieces. Make instant pudding and chill overnight.
In a trifle bowl or glass bowl, place one layer of cake pieces.
Drizzle 1/2 of Kahlua over cake pieces.
Place 1/2 pudding on top, then place 1/2 Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle Heath bits.
Repeat layers again and refrigerate.

title: katie's salad
directions: In a 9 x 11-inch pan, layer lettuce.
Spread cheese over lettuce.
Mix mayonnaise well with lettuce and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In separate pan, slice tomatoes.
Pour approximately 4 ounces Italian dressing over tomatoes. Refrigerate overnight.

title: candlelight chicken(chicken breast with asparagus and carrots)
directions: Bring water to boil; salt to taste.
Cut off and discard tough base of the asparagus spears; clean and set aside.
Julienne the carrot.
Drop vegetables into boiling water approximately 4 minutes; do not overcook.
Drain well.
Set aside.

title: hamburger chile
directions: Brown hamburger with garlic, salt & pepper. Sprinkle flour into browned meat and brown. Add water and tomato sauce. Add green chile and simmer, stirring until thickened. Add red chile if needed for flavoring. (Leftover coffee from this mornings pot is secret ingredient, approx 1/2 C.)

title: cherry supreme
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch dish with Pam.
Place cherry pie filling in dish.
Top with pineapple, juice included.
Spread the dry cake mix over the pineapple.
Sprinkle the nuts over the cake mix. Pour the melted oleo over the nuts.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Fry in deep fat.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Combine sauteed ingredients with all other ingredients except cheese. Place in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Heat in 350° oven until bubbly, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: onion bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix egg and milk. Saute onion in shortening until golden.
Blend in biscuit mix with shortening and egg.
Add onion and half of cheese.
Spread dough in greased glass baking dish.
Sprinkle top with the remaining cheese and with poppy seed.
Sprinkle melted butter over all. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans 15 minutes; drain.
Put half of beans in the bottom of casserole.
Add half of mushroom soup.
Cover with cheese.
Pour half of crushed crackers over cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 10 to 15 servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Blend peanut butter, sugar and margarine.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Roll into walnut-shaped balls (you may need to refrigerate dough first for easier handling).
In a double boiler, melt both chocolates and wax.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture with smooth edge tongs and quickly place on foil or waxed paper. Once cooled, store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Beat egg yolks until they're lighter in color and the consistency of runny mayonnaise.
Add mustard, pepper and salt; beat in well.
Now start adding the oil about 1/2 teaspoon at a time, beating constantly at medium speed until 1/2 cup has been added.
At this point you can stop beating for a few minutes.
If you stop before that it will separate.
Now add the remaining 1 1/2 cups of oil the same way, in small amounts beating constantly until all the oil has been added.
I wait until it's finished to add the lemon juice then you can adjust to your own taste.
Just beat enough to mix after adding lemon juice; I also add a little more salt usually to bring out the flavor.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken, chilies, onion and cheese.
Roll in tortilla shells.
Cover with mixture of 2 cans of cream of chicken soup and 1 can sour cream.
Cover with foil and bake until hot and bubbly at 350°.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and stir well.
Add milk slowly and cook until thick.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Serve over seasoned boiled vegetables.
May add water if needed.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water, margarine and salt in saucepan.
Cook until mixture is brittle when tested in cold water.
Add vanilla.
Pour in fine stream over popcorn, tossing lightly with a large fork to coat evenly.
Grease fingers; shape mixture into balls, pressing popcorn together lightly.
Yields about 3 dozen balls.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix seasonings together and add squash mixture.
Bring to boil and cook 20 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Makes 10 to 11 pints.

title: german apple pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together flour, sugar and salt. Beat eggs with milk and cream; add melted butter.
Combine mixtures and beat until smooth (or mix in blender).
Heat a 10-inch ovenproof skillet and brush well with butter.
Pour 3/4 cup of the batter into the pan, tipping so it flows evenly over the bottom.
When pancake is set, cover with a layer of apples and dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar and bake in oven for 3 minutes.
Fold pancake so apples are inside; sprinkle top with cinnamon sugar and place on a fireproof plate.
Repeat procedure until all 6 pancakes are done, then slip them under the broiler until browned.
Makes 6 pancakes.

title: lazy-day stew
directions: Place roast and vegetables in large casserole.
Mix soups and water and pour over roast.
Seal tightly with foil and bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
Delicious!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease one loaf pan or two one pound
coffee
tins.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add	eggs, oil and pumpkin.	Add
nuts
and raisins.
Bake in 325° oven for an hour and 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add seasoning mix, water and beans and simmer.
Combine lettuce, tomatoes, onion, cheese and dressing. Serve immediately or chill both mixtures until serving time.
Just before serving, combine both mixtures with corn chips.
Mix well and serve.

title: orange roughy
directions: Place fish in shallow baking dish.
Pour orange juice on top and dot with margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Fish is done when it flakes with fork.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute in oil until tender the onion and celery.
Add broccoli. Cook until tender.
Add rice, soup, water and Cheez Whiz.
Stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Put in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: spaghetti salad 1(good!)
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except salad dressing. After all ingredients are mixed and tossed, add half bottle dressing and toss.
Chill.
Just before serving, add remaining dressing and mix.
Recipe makes 8 servings.
Ultra low-fat.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Beat warm cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Stir in mini chocolate chips.
Spoon into crust. Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping, chocolate shavings or fruit.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Drain fruit; reserve liquid from fruit.
Put instant pudding mix in bowl and use liquid from fruit.
Stir until lumps are dissolved.
Chill and serve.
Much better if chilled about 2 hours before serving.

title: pineapple passion
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and run at high speed until pineapple is finely crushed.
While blender is running, add 6 ice cubes, one at a time.
Trim glasses with lemon wedge.

title: pawnee green apple pie
directions: Place apples in pie shell.
Add cinnamon, sugar, nutmeg, few drops lemon juice and few dabs butter over.
Put top crust on and bake at 350°.

title: pinwheel cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy; add egg yolk, milk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add gradually to creamed mixture.
Divide dough into halves and add chocolate to one half.
Roll white dough into a thin sheet.
Roll chocolate dough the same.
Place chocolate dough over white dough and press gently.
Roll up as for a jelly roll, approximately 2-inches in diameter.
Set in icebox for several hours to firm.
Cut into thin slices and bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain excess grease from beef mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook and simmer.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or Fritos.

title: strawberry pretzel jello salad
directions: Cream oleo and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Add pretzels.
Spread in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Take out of oven and cool well.

title: pennsylvania red cabbage
directions: Heat margarine in skillet; add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mayonnaise(old fashion)
directions: Beat the egg, add the flour, salt and sugar.
Stir until well mixed.
Add the vinegar and water.
Cook until almost transparent. Perfect for potato salad.
Add a little extra sugar for apple salad.

title: marie's never fail pie crust
directions: Crumble flour, salt and shortening, then add egg, water and vinegar, making a soft dough.
This dough freezes very well.

title: copenhagen cabbage
directions: Brown meat, spices and onion.
Layer with cabbage and tomato sauce.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 400°.

title: scalloped cherry tomatoes(microwave oven)
directions: Place onion in a bowl.
Add 1 tablespoon of water.
Cover. Microwave 2 1/2 minutes.
Wash tomatoes; place in 1-quart casserole.
Add onion, salt, pepper, thyme, oregano and sugar. Mix well.

title: strawberry soda cake
directions: Combine and mix
all
ingredients
in
a
mixing
bowl. Butter and flour
a Bundt cake pan, then pour ingredients into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ham and cheese pie
directions: Cut lean country style ribs or spareribs into serving pieces. Place on a rack in a shallow baking pan.
On each rib, place 1 slice of lemon and 1 slice of onion.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.
Baste with Houston barbecue sauce, low-fat version, and continue baking 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender. Turn and baste as needed.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and roll in nuts. Chill for several hours before serving.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Put hash browns in 9x13 pan. Drizzle over melted butter. Bake 425 degrees for 35-40 minutes. Remove from oven add meat. Combine cheeses, eggs and milk. Pour over top of hash brown and bake for 30-45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: caramel pecan roll
directions: Combine brown sugar, granulated sugar, salt and milk in small saucepan; bring to a boil and cook to the soft ball stage (242°), stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in butter; cool. Add vanilla and beat and stir in butter.
Cool.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture is firm enough to knead.

title: saltimboca
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on chicken breasts.
Saute in 4 tablespoons butter.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Remove from skillet and place in greased casserole.
Melt remaining 4 tablespoons butter in same skillet; blend in flour and slowly stir in wine and cream. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add diced ham and mushrooms over chicken.
Pour sauce over and bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with rice.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream the sugars, margarine and peanut butter.
Add egg.
Add flour mixture.
Form into balls.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Melt oleo and blend in flour, sugar, salt and milk.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Pour over cabbage and bake at 350° for 1 1/1 hours.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix pineapple, orange slices and cottage cheese.
Pour dry jello over mixture; stir well.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour on flat container.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: tomato aspic salad
directions: Soften the gelatine in 1/4 cup tomato juice.
Stir over low heat until dissolved.
Add 1 cup tomato juice and the salad dressing.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in the green pepper, celery and green onion.
Shrimp meat may be added, if desired.
Pour into salad mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold onto greens; garnish with avocado slices.

title: horehound candy
directions: Make a strong infusion of 1/2 cup of dried horehound steeped in 2 cups boiling water in covered teapot.
Strain after 10 minutes into a 6-quart saucepan.
Add 3 cups sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Boil hard to tack stage, 300°.
Pour into buttered pan. Make into squares before entirely hard to break when it can be handled.
Sift powdered sugar over chunks to keep separate; store in tin box.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter in frypan for 15 minutes.
Place onions in crock-pot with water and salt.
Cook on high for 3 hours.
Put a slice of French bread into each of 4 ovenproof bowls.
Pour soup on top.
Cover with slices of Mozzarella and Swiss cheese.
Broil in oven until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: mushroom and barley soup
directions: I devised this recipe because we grow shiitake mushrooms.

title: anytime snack
directions: Mix all ingredients together and enjoy.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all vegetables well. Mix all vegetables and set aside. Bring sugar, oil and vinegar to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes, cool. Pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: greek-style cucumber and tomato salad
directions: Wash the tomatoes and slice into 3/8-inch thick rounds.
Peel the cucumber and slice diagonally into 1/4-inch thick ovals.
Peel the onion and slice 1/4-inch thick, then separate into rings. Arrange all of these vegetables attractively on a serving plate. Sprinkle with black olives.

title: low-fat white clam sauce for linguine(makes about 4 servings)
directions: Mix the cornstarch with about 1/4 cup of the clam juice and set it aside.
Combine everything except the linguine and the cheese in a saucepan and simmer, covered, about 5 minutes, then stir in the cornstarch mixture which will thicken the sauce only slightly.
Simmer another 5 minutes, stirring.
When the sauce clears, pour it over your still warm linguine.
For the more high-fat version, add 2 tablespoons good olive oil to the sauce, and use the cheese more liberally.

title: crusty baked potatoes
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Brush potatoes with mixture. Place cut side down on baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pink stuff salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together (well) and chill.
Serves 6.

title: potato croquettes
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Drop by spoonful into hot oil. Brown; drain on paper towel.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together shortening and sugar. Add molasses and beaten eggs; stir until creamy.
Add salt, baking soda and spices; stir.
Add flour; stir.
Roll cookies in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for about 15 minutes at 375°.

title: frozen lemon torte
directions: Line ice cube tray, 9x5 inch loaf pan or 8 inch sq pan with half the crumbs.
In medium saucepan, combine the egg yolks (reserve whites in small mixer bowl), lemon peel, lemon juice, 1/4 C sugar and the salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, till mixture just bubbles.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken 1/2 hour with salt.
Save 2 cups broth.
Pick chicken into small pieces.
Place in bottom of an 11 x 9-inch greased casserole.
Add milk to soup; pour over chicken.
Add 2 cups broth to stuffing; toss well.
Spread evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: japanese fruit pies
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Divide batter filling into 3 shells.
Place in oven, set at 300°, for 10 minutes.
Turn oven down to 275°.
Cook for 35 minutes.

title: cherry cream freeze
directions: Blend ingredients. Add Cool Whip. Put into a 9 x 5-inch pan. Cover with foil and freeze 24 hours.

title: berries in the snow
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together.
Put layer of this mixture in the bottom of a bowl.
Layer cookies and berries; continue, and end with Cool Whip mixture on top.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients.
Add soups and rice.
Mix.
Bake in covered casserole 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese, if desired.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.
Freezes well.

title: moms aunt sally's cookies
directions: Mix well, chill for 1 hour.
Roll out but not to thin.
The cut with a empty spam can.
Bake in 350 degrees till brown 12- 15 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Place lemon juice in milk to equal 2/3 cup.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, place sifted flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add shortening, bananas and sour milk mixture.
Beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Add eggs.
Beat for 2 more minutes. Add walnuts, if desired.
Bake in a Bundt pan in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool 1 minute in pan, then turn out on plate.
May be iced.

title: barbecue chicken in mustard sauce
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour or 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain and mash yams.
Mix all ingredients and pour into greased 11 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.

title: pasta with carbonara sauce
directions: Let eggs, butter or margarine and cream stand at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours.
Beat together eggs and cream just until blended.
Add pasta to a large amount of boiling salted water.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain well.
Heat an ovenproof serving dish in a 250° oven.

title: taco rice
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onion.
Add seasoning, tomatoes and rice.
Take off heat and add cheese.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush Oreos and mix with butter.
Press in cake pan, reserving 1 cup.
Beat 1 container of Cool Whip with cream cheese and place on cookie crust.
Mix pudding with milk and place on whipped topping mixture.
Top with remaining whipped topping and reserved crumbs.

title: goetta
directions: Boil the meats seasoned with salts in enough water to yield about 2 quarts of stock.
When tender, remove the meat and remove all bones, gristle, fat, skin and other objectionable objects. Chop meat against grain into chunks (1/2-inch or less)
Heat stock; when boiling, add oats, stirring well to prevent sticking. Add water or oats as necessary to make mixture barely stiff.

title: mexicali corn dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding cumin and sauce to taste.

title: fruit stuffing
directions: Place chicken bouillon cube in water; bring to a boil and stir until dissolved.
Add margarine and allow to melt.
Pour water mixture over bread stuffing and toss lightly with a fork.
Add fruit and toss again.
Add beaten eggs and fold into stuffing mixture.
Stuff mixture into chicken, turkey or duck or bake as dressing in a pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together oil, sugar and salt.
Add eggs and beat. Combine remaining ingredients with creamed mixture.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour in center of oven.
Turn out to cool.
Wrap in waxed paper.
(Note:
Burns easily.)

title: bits o' brickle ice cream pie
directions: Spread half of ice cream into pie shell.
Sprinkle Bits O' Brickle on top.
Heap with remaining ice cream.
Freeze.
To serve, stir sauce well and spoon over individual pieces of pie.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, then add all other ingredients.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: cabbage
directions: Chop pepper, onion and garlic; saute in oil and butter for a few minutes.
Add rest of ingredients; stir.
Cut cabbage into fourths; cut core out.
Cover skillet and cook on low, stirring often, for about 30 to 45 minutes.
May have to add a little more water.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar and water (plus juice from the berry can).
Cook 5 minutes.
Put in pan.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder, 2 tablespoons sugar, shortening and milk to form dough. Roll dough 1/3-inch thick and spread berries on and dot with cinnamon and butter.
Roll up like a jelly roll and cut in 1-inch slices and put on top of juice in pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
You may use any other type fruit.

title: cristy's heath bars
directions: Put tinfoil over large cookie sheet.
Butter foil.
Lay crackers over foiled cookie sheet.
Boil 1 cup brown sugar and 1 cup butter for 15 minutes.
Pour over saltine crackers.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Melt chocolate and pour over.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate at least 1/2 hour.

title: aunt sandy's waffles
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Combine all ingredients and let rise 45 minutes.
Bake appropriate amount of batter in a heated waffle iron.
Serve with maple syrup or applesauce or fresh blueberries and cream or fresh strawberries and cream or fresh peaches and cream.

title: low calorie spaghetti squash marinara
directions: Halve squash lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds.
Place squash, cut side down, in a baking dish.
With a fork, prick the skin all over.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef on High for 5 or 6 minutes in the microwave. Add 1/2 jar picante sauce and refried beans to ground beef mixture.
Stir well.
Place chips on a glass tray.
Pour ground beef mixture over chips.
Sprinkle with cheese on top.
Melt 2 minutes on High in the microwave.
Garnish with tomatoes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onions and butter together.
Add other ingredients and cook slow until it thickens.
Stir often.
Makes 1 quart.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and the 1 cup sugar until light.
Add vanilla and egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the water, beating after each addition.
Gradually add the egg whites and remaining sugar, beating to stiff peaks. Fold into batter; blend well.
Turn into two greased and lightly floured 8 x 1 1/2-inch round layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine sugar, flour and melted margarine.
Stir until well blended.
Add peaches and juice.
Pour mixture into a baking dish, cook at 400° until golden brown.

title: jalapeno corn
directions: Heat corn.
Add entire contents of Philly cream cheese.
Add 1/4 cup of minced jalapeno.
Heat over low heat for about 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Boil yams until soft.
Peel and mash together with butter until smooth.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add granulated sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and milk.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° until marshmallows are golden brown.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Wash and
chop
lettuce.
Let drain well, then place in large bowl.
Add the chopped onion, tomatoes, cheese, avocado, Catalina dressing, hot sauce and Doritos.
Toss gently to mix.

title: blond brownies
directions: Melt oleo and brown sugar over low heat.
Add next 6 ingredients.
(You may put chips on top or stir in.)
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil; beat 1 minute.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, soda, salt and cocoa together.
Add to mixture with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add vinegar and food coloring.
Bake at 350° for 24 minutes.

title: spinach stir-fry with almonds
directions: Don't overcook and you will enjoy this recipe even if you don't like cooked spinach.

title: date bread
directions: Day 1:
Receive 1 cup starter.
Put in container with tight lid.
Do not refrigerate.

title: tomato vegetable soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, bring tomatoes, broth and water to boil.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Return to boil.
Reduce to simmer and cook about 1 hour or until vegetables are tender. Yield:
about 5 3/4 cups.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening, and sugar. Add sifted flour and baking powder to mixture. Alternating with milk, ending with flour. Add flavorings. Mix 1/4 c. flour with nuts, add to mixture. Blend and pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix boiling water and jello.
Cook together cranberries, sugar and a little water.
When the two mixtures have cooled, then mix together and add the apples and pineapple.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix popcorn, M&M's and nuts together in a large bowl. In a saucepan, melt margarine, marshmallows and oil together. Pour over popcorn mixture and mix well with a large spoon or hands. Spray bundt pan with non-stick
cooking spray and pack mixture tightly into pan. Let sit overnight or 3 hours before removing from pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Make broccoli according to package directions; drain well and set aside.
Combine milk, 4 tablespoons butter and flour over low heat (will be thin).
Melt cheese into sauce.
Heat water until hot; melt 1 stick butter into it.
Add stuffing.
Turn off heat. Add celery and onion.
Layer broccoli, stuffing and sauce in greased casserole dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place potatoes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Season with salt and pepper.

In a bowl, add minced onions and mix together sour cream and cream of chicken soup; mix these items together. Pour soup mixture over potatoes; sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and butter that you have cut into cubes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until all is completely warm and cheese is melted.

title: two potato swirls
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
In separate saucepans cook white potatoes and sweet potatoes in a small amount of boiling salted water, covered, about 20 minutes or until they are tender.
Drain. In a small mixer bowl beat hot white potatoes with an electric mixer on low speed until almost smooth.
Add 1 tablespoon of margarine or butter and milk.
Continue beating until light and fluffy.
Transfer to another bowl.
In same mixer bowl, beat hot sweet potatoes with an electric mixer on low until almost smooth. Add remaining margarine or butter, orange juice and honey. Continue beating until light and fluffy.
Line a baking sheet with foil; spray with nonstick spray coating.
Spoon white potato mixture along one side of a decorating bag fitted with a large star tip.
Spoon sweet potato mixture along other side of bag.
For swirls on the prepared baking sheet, pipe 3-inch circles of the mixture, starting at the outside and working toward the center, building a peak 2 layers high.

title: pumpkin muffins(makes 18 muffins or 1 large loaf)
directions: If you can't afford Mrs. Powell's, try this recipe!

title: orange muffins
directions: In blender, puree the orange and orange juice together. Add to remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12 to 16.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy in medium-sized bowl.
Beat in whole eggs and yolks.
Sift flour with baking soda and nutmeg.
Add to batter.
Fold in nuts.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour but not longer than overnight.
Roll into teaspoon-sized balls and place on buttered cookie sheet.
Gently flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sprinkling mixture, then lightly sift additional mixture over each cookie with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until bottoms are lightly done, not brown.
Remove from cookie sheet while still warm and cool on wax paper-covered rack.
Store in airtight container with a couple pieces of bread in the bottom.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Begin simmering beans in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Saute the sausage and ham hock.
Saute the vegetables in meat renderings until translucent.
Add all remaining ingredients to beans and saute until tender approximately 2 hours.
Keep covered with water.
Mash some beans for creaminess.
Serve over rice.
Add chicken stock, if desired.

title: snow cream
directions: Stir enough milk into snow to get ice cream consistency.
Add vanilla.
Add enough sugar to sweeten.
Eat immediately.
Freeze any extra in small containers.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add 7-Up and let stand until slightly set.
Add pineapple, banana and marshmallows.

title: sunday pork roast
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons flour, salt, pepper, bay leaf and thyme; rub over entire roast. Place roast with fat side up in a shallow roasting pan. Arrange vegetables around the roast. Pour 2 cups cold water into pan. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, basting with pan juices every 30 minutes. Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake 30 minutes longer or until a meat thermometer reads 160°. Remove roast to a serving platter; keep warm. Strain pan drippings, reserving the broth; discard vegetables. Add water to the broth to measure 1 2/3 cups. Return to pan. Combine remaining flour and cold water until smooth, stir into pan. Bring to a boil, cook and stir for 2 minutes. Serve with the roast.

title: hush puppies
directions: Add enough buttermilk to mix stiff batter.
Spoon into deep pan of hot oil.
Cook at 350° until done.
Yields 24 hush puppies.

title: quick  tortellini and spinach soup
directions: Heat the oil over medium-high heat. Add garlic and onion. Cook 10 to 15 minutes until browned. Add broth and herbs.

Boil and stir in tortellini. Simmer, uncovered, 10 to 12 minutes. Stir in crushed tomatoes; simmer 5 minutes. Add spinach and cook until wilted, about 3 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve with cheese on top.
Great with sourdough rolls.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown chicken in butter (lightly).
Add sausage and cook with lid on.
Add onions, garlic, celery, salt and red and black pepper. Cook over medium heat with lid on.
Put in a tablespoon of vegetable oil and mix.
Cook down until onions are invisible.
Add tomato sauce and mix.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Reserve 2 cups chicken broth; set aside.

title: pumpkin bundt cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients (flour, sugar and cinnamon) with eggs, oil, pumpkin and nuts and mix.
Place ingredients in an already greased and lightly floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apricot glaze meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, oats, eggs, onions, 1/4 cup catsup, milk, Worcestershire sauce, horseradish, salt and pepper; mix well. Pack into lightly oiled ring mold.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. Let stand in pan 5 minutes.

title: louisville hot brown
directions: To
make sauce, melt butter in pan.
Stir in flour; add milk. Cook until mixture thickens.
Add cheese and stir until melted. Lay
turkey
slices
on
toast.
Top with bacon, then pour	cheese sauce over bacon.
Bake under broiler until sauce begins to brown.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix together melted butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add unsweetened chocolate, sifted flour and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into a well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Makes about 8 servings.
Slice in wedges.
These are similar to brownies.

title: easy pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift in remaining ingredients. Allow to rest 5 minutes.
Pat on 2 baking sheets.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat the oven at 350°.
Mix all ingredients together. Grease the pan.
Let cake bake for 45 minutes, then let it cool off.

title: oatmeal carmoletes
directions: Stir caramels and 1/2 cup evaporated milk in saucepan until melted.
Mix.

title: irish scone
directions: s. While kneading, gradually add 1 1/4 cups buttermilk.
Knead well.
Grease and flour frying pan or cookie sheet.
Place batter in frying pan and shape into mound.
Spread buttermilk on top and add a little sugar.
Snip a cross on top with scissors.
Bake at 400° for first 10 minutes and at 350° for 30 more minutes.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Mix
jello,
water,
sugar and cream cheese.
While half set, stir in pineapple, 7-Up and vanilla.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix and serve hot.
Do not boil.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Combine soy sauce,
wine,
oil and ginger.
(A bottle of prepared teriyaki
sauce
can
be
substituted for this.) Place chicken breasts, skin side
down, in a dish deep enough to hold sauce.
Pour lemon
juice
over
breasts.
Next pour sauce over the meat.
Sprinkle
teaspoon
brown sugar over each chicken breast.
Cover and let marinate for 2 to 3 hours, turning every 15 to 20
minutes.
Cook on charcoal grill, turning and basting often.
For juicier chicken, cook with skin on.

title: ham, egg breakfast stir-fry
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk until nearly smooth; set aside. Preheat wok to medium heat.
Add 1 tablespoon oil.
Add half of eggs.
Lift tilt the wok to form a thin sheet of egg.
Cook, without stirring, about 2 minutes or until egg sheet is set.
Slide egg sheet onto a cutting board.
Cut into 3/4 inch wide strips. Repeat with remaining eggs, adding more cooking oil if necessary. Stir-fry chopped onion in 1 tablespoon hot oil 30 seconds.
Add green pepper; stir 1 minute.
Add ham and mushrooms; stir 1 to 2 minutes.
Add rice; cook 1 minute.
Stir in egg strips.
Stir in cream cheese mixture; toss to coat.
Cover; cook 1 minute.

title: skipper casserole(tuna)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Sprinkle cheese over spaghetti.
Combine and beat together remaining ingredients.
Pour over spaghetti and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, covered the first 15 minutes.
After baked, use your favorite sauce and meatballs.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel, core, and chop apples
into small pieces.
Pour sugar over apples. Add nuts.
Let stand at least 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together peanut butter, shortening, brown sugar, and sugar. Add eggs and mix well. Add baking powder and flour. Beat with an electric mixer at high speed until all is well mixed. Roll into small balls. Place on a greased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork to make a crisscross pattern on each cookie. Bake for 15 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Mix and cool boiling water and cocoa.
Beat and separate eggs. Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
May add red food coloring.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread.
Chill.
Take round bread, cut out center and leave bottom.
Use as serving bowl. Bread from center can be dipped and eaten.

title: sugar n' spice cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Sift together and stir in flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and pecans.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into balls the size of small walnuts.
Place about 2-inches apart on a greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in moderate oven (350°). Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: bacon zucchini quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In a large frying pan, fry bacon until crispy. Remove from pan and drain on paper towels.
Pour out all bacon fat except 2 tablespoons.
Saute zucchini and onion in bacon fat over medium heat until tender, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, mix together eggs, milk, cheeses and pepper. Spread zucchini mixture in bottom of an uncooked pastry shell. Sprinkle bacon pieces over the zucchini mixture.
Pour the egg mixture into the pastry shell and bake for 15 minutes at 450°.
Turn oven heat down to 350° and bake for another 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Serve warm or cold.
Serves 8.

title: salmon lasagne
directions: Combine salmon, spinach, scallions, eggs, cheeses, salt and nutmeg.
Spread on noodles, roll up and set aside.
Pour half of cheese sauce into bottom of baking pan.
Place lasagne in baking dish.
Cover with remaining cheese sauce.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: messy muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add oil, egg and then milk.
Spoon in muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Roll in melted butter or margarine, then roll in sugar mixed with 1 1/2 teaspoons of cinnamon.

title: holly jolly punch
directions: Mix together and chill.
May chill before mixing.
This recipe makes 1 regular size punch bowl full.

title: bread
directions: Warm milk and melt butter.
Dissolve yeast in a little milk. Mix all and knead.
Let rise.
When doubled in bulk, knead down again and let rise.
When done, cut bread to size and let rise in pans overnight.
Place in oven (preheated to 400°), then lower to 200°.
Bake for 1 hour, depending on size of bread.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add granulated and brown sugars, and cream together until mixture is light and fluffy. Add vanilla, egg and beat again until light and fluffy. Sift flour once; measure, add salt and soda and sift again. Add flour mixture, in two parts, until well mixed into batter. Add M&M candies and nuts. Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Blend all ingredients by hand in a bowl until thoroughly mixed.
Pinch off into small balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press down with a fork and bake at 325° or until faintly colored.
Make about 48 balls.

title: ham appetillas
directions: Lay tortillas out to warm.
Combine all ingredients except ham. Spread a thin layer on tortillas.
Arrange 2 to 4 ham slices on cheese layer.
Roll up tightly.
Wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
To serve, cut into 3/4-inch slices.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain and mash.
Add other ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Put in casserole dish and cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: summer chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, combine sugar and salt; add syrup.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Beat eggs until foamy.
When syrup is hot, add butter and stir until melts.
Add vanilla, pecans and eggs.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for about 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine the three cheeses.
Add 1 small minced onion, 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Roll in finely chopped parsley.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown in hot fat
onion, add meat and seasoning; brown. Add drained beans and
soup.
Grease
bowl
and mash potatoes. Add milk, egg and seasoning.
Spoon in mounds over meat.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed eggplant rolls
directions: Peel eggplant.
Slice lengthwise.
Dip slices into egg, then bread crumbs.
Fry until golden.
Lay on paper towels.
Place a scoop of Ricotta in middle of each eggplant slice.
Top with slice of Mozzarella, then roll eggplant.
Secure with toothpicks.
Place eggplant in greased, shallow baking pan.
Top with sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 30 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: lime and honey broiled chicken
directions: Combine lime juice, margarine, honey and garlic powder in a small saucepan.
Heat until margarine is melted.
Stir in wine. Line a small shallow baking pan with foil; arrange chicken in pan, skin side up.
Pour lime juice mixture over chicken and let stand 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Broil 10 to 15 minutes; turn and baste with juice.
Broil additional 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
Serves 2.

title: orange salad
directions: Stir all together and cool in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: magnificent mexican dip
directions: Layer
ingredients
in order listed.
Heat in microwave until hot and bubbly and cheese is thoroughly melted.
Serves 8.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all together. Pour in Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Heat a small amount of oil in a large skillet on medium-high heat. Add chicken. Cook 5 minutes on each side or until cooked through. Remove from skillet. Add soup and 1 cup water; bring to a boil. Stir in rice and broccoli. Top with chicken and cheese. Cover. Cook on low heat 5 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Mix flour and ginger.
Lay out chicken breast and beat slightly with dull knife.
Lay slice of ham and then slice of cheese on top of chicken breast.
Roll it up, then roll in flour mixture, stick toothpick through it to hold roll.

title: pineapple punch
directions: In pan, combine water, cinnamon and cloves.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Strain into large pitcher and cool.
Add sugar and juices, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Chill.
Just before serving, pour into punch bowl and slowly pour in soda.

title: cucumber snack
directions: Mix together; spread over bread.
Slice cucumber; place on bread.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper.

title: easy mint tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags, cover and steep 5 minutes. Remove tea bags, squeezing gently.
Add sugar and lemon juice, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Stir in 3 quarts water, pineapple juice and ginger ale. Serve over ice.
Yields about 1 1/2 gallons.

title: "good luck" bean soup
directions: Wash beans thoroughly.
Place in kettle.
Cover with water. Add 2 teaspoons salt.
Soak overnight.
Then drain off soaking water.
Add to the beans 2 quarts water, ham, ham bone, ham hocks, sausage or turkey sausage.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer slowly for 3 hours.
Then add all other ingredients.
Simmer another 45 minutes.
This soup improves upon standing.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, salt, flour and baking powder alternately with buttermilk. Stir in nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes for layers; 75 minutes for tube pan.

title: holiday trail mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Trail Mix will keep up to 2 weeks in a closed container in the refrigerator.

title: dandy shandy
directions: Place dark stout beer in a serving glass.
Pour ginger ale atop. Makes 1 (8-ounce) serving.

title: blueberry crepes
directions: Reserve crepes.
Combine cornstarch, sugar replacement, salt, milk, lemon juice and vanilla in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until slightly thickened; remove from heat.
Crush 1 cup (250 ml) of the blueberries and add to cream mixture.
Return to heat and cook and stir until thickened.
Cool.
Fold in remaining blueberries.
Divide evenly between crepes and fold or roll the crepes.
Top each with heaping 1 tablespoon (15 ml) topping.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange. Combine and set aside. In a small bowl, combine gelatin, sugar and boiling water. Stir to dissolve gelatin and sugar. Cool slightly. Add cranberries, orange and crushed pineapple. Fold together all ingredients. Pour into serving dish or mold. Chill until firm.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Combine chicken, vinegar, lemon juice, soy sauce, onion, bay leaves, peppercorns and garlic in covered non-aluminum saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring gently.
Reduce heat and simmer until chicken is tender, about 50 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: saucy meatballs and macaroni
directions: Mix ground beef gently with egg, crumbs, milk, salt and pepper.
Shape into medium-sized meatballs and put into greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Wash and slice zucchini 1/2-inch thick.
Add onions, peppers and garlic.
Add salt and cover with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly. Let stand 3 hours; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over squash mixture.
Heat just to a boil.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 8 pints.
Ripe pimento may be added for color.

title: oklahoma dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies; place half on the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix the cream cheese, margarine and sugar together in separate bowl.
Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and cream cheese mixture.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle top with other half of the cookies.
Chill or freeze.

title: mint surprises
directions: Mix together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and add sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs, water and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to the creamed ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least two hours.
Enclose a chocolate/mint wafer in about 2 tablespoons dough.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: green beans and beef
directions: Brown ground chuck, then add onion, bell pepper and cubed potatoes.
When potatoes begin to get tender, add green beans, salt and pepper to your liking and cook until beans are cooked. Delicious.

title: pickles
directions: Bring water, vinegar and ice cream salt to boil and put in bottom of jar these ingredients:
garlic bud and hot pepper to your taste.
Pour hot vinegar over pickles.
Heat and seal in a hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease large cookie sheet.
In a large skillet, cook and stir onion and garlic in oil until onion is tender.
Add chicken.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes.
