Slice potatoes thinly.
Put potatoes and brown sugar in hot oil.
Turn potatoes often.
Fry for 30 to 40 minutes on medium heat.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine ingredients in a food processor
until
smooth. Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: corn bread stuffing(will stuff a 5 to 6 pound fowl)
directions: Can use chicken broth instead of water.
Can use cooked giblets.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix catsup, brown sugar, vinegar, liquid smoke and salt and pepper; add to beans.
Brown hamburger, drain and set aside. Saute onion.
Cook bacon; drain.
Add to bean mixture.
Simmer in crock-pot.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar and eggs. Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add first and second ingredients; mix well.
Roll into ball.
Roll in sugar. Place on cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: green chili pie
directions: Press green chilies in bottom of pie pan.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Beat eggs in milk; pour over top.
Add hot sauce.
Bake at 400° to 425° until lightly brown, approximately 20 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Pour sugar, dates and butter in top of double boiler (over hot water).
Leave over hot water until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut, nuts and Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls. Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: lavon's banana pudding
directions: Layer in a large bowl with bananas and vanilla wafers.
Last layer should be bananas and vanilla wafers on top.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add slightly frozen strawberries with juice and mashed bananas.
Add pineapple with juice.
Pour half mixture into 9 x 11 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Keep remaining jello at room temperature.
Spread sour cream on set mixture.
Add remaining jello over sour cream.
Chill until set.

title: ruby slipper cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream, water and eggs.
Blend and then beat 2 minutes at medium speed.

title: school cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in lukewarm water.
Add melted shortening and beaten egg.
Add flour, powdered milk and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover and let rise until double.
Work down and roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Brush with butter, sprinkle with cinnamon mix and roll up lengthwise.
Cut into 12 (2 1/2-inch thick) rolls. Place on greased tray and let rise until double.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Brush with powdered sugar glaze.

title: finger jello
directions: Stir together first 2 ingredients; let stand.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring this to a boil; add first mixture to this.
Pour in a long cake pan and refrigerate.

title: laverne's crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix.
Make a day early.

title: hash brown hamburger casserole
directions: Press hamburger in bottom of casserole dish. Spread mushroom soup over hamburger. Arrange Tots over soup
until soup is covered. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage squares
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage with onion; drain.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Spread on rye squares and place on cookie sheet.
Put in freezer until firm.
Store in Ziploc bags in freezer until ready to use.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: super brownies
directions: In a double boiler over hot water, stirring often, melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from range and double boiler bottom; reserve.
In a medium bowl, stir together flour and sugar; add eggs and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Add reserved chocolate mixture and beat to blend.
Fold in pecans.
Turn into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean, about 25 minutes. Loosen edges; cool and cut into squares.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, sour cream, 1/2 of Cool Whip and milk.
Beat until fluffy.
Alternate bananas in layers with wafers and pudding mix. Top with rest of Cool Whip.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, flour and salt.
Beat egg yolks; add milk.
Gradually blend in all ingredients with eggs.
Cook until mixture thickens; add butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 minutes longer. Turn into pie shell.
Add meringue and cook a few minutes in oven.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Core and cube apples.
(Leave skin on for color).
Pour lemon juice over apples and stir well to coat pieces and prevent them from turning brown.
Let them set 10 minutes or so while preparing other ingredients.	Combine apples, celery, raisins, and walnuts. Mix yogurt, honey and salt.
Stir until well blended.
Add dressing to apple mixture, mix well.
Can serve on lettuce leaves.
Yield: 4 -6 servings.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix and sprinkle the bottom of the pan with coconut and pecans.
Mix the German chocolate cake according to the package directions; pour over coconut/pecan mixture.

title: shortbread from scotland
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pat into a jelly roll pan. Bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: basic icebox yeast dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm water.
Add salt, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Add half the flour and all the melted shortening.
Mix well.
Add remaining flour and knead to a soft dough.
Put in refrigerator.
When doubled, work down.
Grease lightly.
Always keep well covered.
Keeps well for about 5 days.
Can be used for dinner rolls, coffee cake or cinnamon rolls.

title: ocono punch
directions: Mix all juices.
Add ginger ale and almond flavor just before serving.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Steep tea bags in hot water for 5 to 10 minutes; remove bags. Add cold water, sugar, orange and lemon concentrates and bourbon; mix well.
Pour into plastic cups and freeze.
Serve frozen with a spoon.

title: dutch twists
directions: Add cheese to pie crust mix.
Prepare according to directions. Roll dough 1/4-inch thick.
Brush with egg white; sprinkle with salt and nutmeg.
Cut in strips 1/2 x 5-inches.
Twist and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: easy sweet crispy dill pickles
directions: Rinse pickles with cold water after taking off juice and drain again.
Cut into slices and put in one or more jars.
Make syrup with vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add ground allspice and pour over pickles. Add a clove of garlic to each jar.
Put jars in refrigerator. They are ready to eat in 2 days.
Very good!

title: apricot jello "dessert"
directions: Prepare jello as directed on box.
Drain the crushed pineapple. Add 1/2 cup pineapple and the small marshmallows to jello and set.
Take the beaten egg and add flour, pineapple juice, sugar and butter.
Cook until thick.
Add cream cheese and cool.
Beat Dream Whip and add to cool mixture.
Spread on cold jello and chill.

title: make and freeze beef-tomato sauce
directions: Crumble ground beef into a 3-quart microwave-safe casserole. Add onion, garlic and green pepper.

title: woody's wonderful strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen berries immediately.
Put aside about 5 to 10 minutes, until partially set.
Add the pineapple and nuts.
Pour half in an 8 x 8 glass dish.
Let set.
Stir sour cream into remaining mixture and pour over first layer.
Chill until set.

title: chocolate trinkets
directions: Heat chocolate in
baking dish (9 x 9 x 2-inches) for 5 minutes or just
until soft.
Spread in an even layer.
Sprinkle walnuts on
top,
pressing
in.
Beat egg until foamy in a small bowl.
Beat
in
sugar until well blended.
Mix in coconut. Spread
evenly
on
top
of chocolate-walnut layer.
Cut candied cherries into
1/8-inch
pieces.
Place on top in even rows.
Bake in
moderate
oven
at 350° for 15 minutes or just until coconut topping
is set.
Cool in pan on wire rack;
cut into 1-inch squares;
just leave in pan.
Chill until ready to serve, then cut again and remove.

title: amazing egg custard pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into large pie pan.
Let set for 5 minutes. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine one head of cabbage, chopped fine with green onions. In a small amount of oil, brown sesame seed and almonds, stirring constantly.
Break up Top Ramen noodles.
Reserve seasoning packets for dressing.
Toss together raw noodles, cabbage, onions, almonds and seed.
Add cooked chicken.

title: dip
directions: Mix all together.
Serve with vegetables or chips.

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Beat cream until stiff; add vanilla.
Break Heath bars with hammer until crumbled and add 6 bars to cream and mix.
Save 3 crumbled bars to sprinkle on top.

title: low-fat baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine Ricotta and Mozzarella with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, egg whites, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Cook ziti al dente and drain.
Combine ziti, cheese mix and 3/4 jar of sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish sprayed with low-fat Mazola spray.
Top with remaining sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana walnut bread
directions: Slit
top
off plastic bag containing cake mix and pour in the pudding mix;
blend.
Mix together bananas, cooking oil and water with
eggs,
then beat in the combined cake mix and pudding mix. Beat
at high speed for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in walnuts;
pour into buttered Bundt pan or a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for
50 to 55 minutes, until top is golden brown and cake begins drawing away from sides of pan.

title: orange cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and orange jello.
Add Cool Whip and fruit. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: chocolate chip cookies(uses chocolate chip cookie mix)
directions: Stir the mix to distribute chips and nuts evenly.
Combine with vanilla and eggs.
This creates a heavy batter.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown the hamburger; season to taste.
Add the chopped onion and peppers, if desired.
Add the chili, Cheddar cheese soup, nacho cheese soup and tomato paste to the meat mixture.
Cook on low heat until heated thoroughly, stirring frequently.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: greek salad(elliniki salata)
directions: Wash dry and tear lettuce into pieces.
Place in a large salad bowl that has been rubbed with cut garlic. Cut up remaining vegetables as desired; add to lettuce.
Add salt and pepper and toss.
Serve with dressing that consists of 1 part lemon juice or wine vinegar to 2 parts olive oil.
Garnish with feta cheese, olives and
anchovies. Sprinkle with fresh herbs or dried oregano.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice separately as directed on package. Saute onion and celery in 1/2 stick of oleo.
Combine rice and broccoli with all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
This dish can be frozen.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together sugar, eggs, oil, pumpkin and cinnamon.
In a separate bowl mix together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Then add to wet mixture.
Mix in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake in a greased Bundt or angel food pan for 1 hour.
This cake is very moist so a toothpick won't come clean when you check it.

title: quick apple pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine apples, cinnamon, flour, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well. Fill one of the ready-made pie shells with the apple mixture.
Take the other pie shell out of its tin and put it on top of the apple mixture.
Close the pie up by pressing your fork along the edge.
Poke a few holes in the top of the pie with your fork so that hot air can get out as it bakes.
Bake pie at 375° for one hour or until crust is golden brown.
Cool and serve.

title: plantation punch
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Mix well and serve.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk; add Cool Whip into mixture.
Layer all the ingredients in a large glass dish.
Drizzle syrup over crackers and pudding.

title: microwave rice cake s'mores
directions: Spread peanut butter on rice cake.
Top with chocolate bar and marshmallows.
Microwave 15 seconds.
Let stand 30 seconds.

title: quill's boiled crawfish for a crowd
directions: To clean crawfish, pour 1/2 lb. salt into a large pot of clean water.
Add crawfish to pot and let them sit for 3 to 4 minutes and then drain.

title: pineapple-orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into jello mold. Refrigerate.
To be served with meal.

title: chicken cheese lasagna
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion and garlic in butter until tender. Stir in flour and salt; cook until bubbly.
Gradual ly stir in broth and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in 2 cups Mozzarella, 1/2 cup parmesan cheese, basil, oregano and pepper; set aside.
In a bowl, combine ricotta cheese, parsley and remaining mozzarella; set aside.
Spread one-quarter of the cheese sauce into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish; cover with one- third of the noodles.
Top with half of ricotta mixture, half the spinach, and half of the chicken.
Cover with one-quarter cheese sauce and one-third noodles.
Repeat layers of ricotta mixture, spinach, chicken and one-quarter cheese sauce.
Cover with remaining noodles and cheese sauce.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35-40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Yield 12 servings.

title: texas taters
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 450° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pickled onion relish
directions: Peel onions and slice very thin with mandolin or slicing section of a grater. Separate slices and boil in water for 1 minute. Drain thoroughly. Combine balance of ingredients in glass bowl and add drained onions. Press onions into the marinade with wooden spoon. Cover and let stand at room temperature for 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Store in refrigerator in sealed glass container. Will last for weeks. No limit to its uses. Good with cold meat, fish, poultry, in salads and on sandwiches. Makes 3 cups.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown meat in skillet with onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: ampuckie
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and celery. Cook noodles according to package directions.
Combine beef and noodles; add mushroom soup and catsup.
Heat together and serve.

title: nut fudge
directions: Mix in large glass bowl.
Microwave 5 minutes on High.
Stir and microwave until bubbly on top, about 3 minutes on High.
Stir in vanilla, chocolate chips and nuts.
Set in cold water and stir until it starts to set.
Spread in an 8 x 9-inch buttered pan. May also be cooked over medium heat, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Boil and stir 5 minutes.
Continue with directions. Fudge should cook to soft ball stage.

title: corn pudding
directions: Stir flour, salt, sugar and butter into corn.
Beat eggs well and stir into milk.
Mix together and pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake in a slow oven at 325° for 20 or 25 minutes.
Stir from the bottom 3 times while baking.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Put as listed into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french toast
directions: Mix eggs, salt and milk well.
Dip bread into mixture, coating each side well.
Brown both sides of bread in butter on hot griddle.
Serve hot with syrup, honey or a sprinkling of confectioners sugar.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cover tightly.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl until smooth.
Stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and spices.
Mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Store in refrigerator. Makes 8 servings.

title: creamy cheese potatoes
directions: In medium saucepan, over low heat, blend milk into cream cheese.
If necessary, beat smooth with rotary beater.
Stir in chives, onion and salt.
Add cubed potatoes; stir carefully to coat.

title: meat marinade
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl and use as a marinade for chicken, pork and lamb or on ham before roasting or broiling.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook wild rice as directed; let cool.
Cut up chicken and grapes.
In a large bowl, mix together all ingredients except nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: peach dessert
directions: Mix all the ingredients and press into 9 x 12 dish. Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until lightly brown. Cool completely.

title: chicken breast with sour cream
directions: Mix sour cream, garlic, celery salt, salt, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and paprika.
Coat chicken with this mixture.
Lay in a buttered pan.
Marinate overnight or for several hours.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and place a pat of butter on each.
Cover lightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Check to see if dry; if so, add 1/4 cup water around.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan and top with second crust or pastry strips.
Seal edges and cut slits in top.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hungry jack beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in salt, beans, barbecue sauce, ketchup, brown sugar and onion.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Pull biscuits apart to make 10 instead of 5.
Place on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Put rice on bottom of casserole, then cooked chicken.
Next, add broccoli and pour mushroom soup/mayonnaise mixture over these three ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Take out and add onion rings on top.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: binner's pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook on hot griddle.
Serve with Blackberry Brandy Sauce (below).

title: port wine salad
directions: I would add 2 teaspoons plain gelatin, dissolving in 4 tablespoons of water.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream Judges 5:25 and Jeremiah 6:20.
Chop Nahum 3:12 and add to mixture.
Beat Isaiah 10:14 until frothy and add Judges 4:19. Sift part if 1 Kings 4:22 with Amos 4:5.
Add remaining Kings. Add alternately to cream mixture along with Isaiah 10:14.
Beat well.
Add 1 Samuel 14:25, 1 Samuel 30:12 and Numbers 17:8.
Add to mixture with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 375° until tests done.

title: fancy kreplach
directions: Combine flour, salt and oil.
In a separate bowl, beat egg yolks, water and baking powder (or soda).
Add to flour mixture. Knead and roll out, thinly, on floured surface.
Cut into 3-inch squares or circles.

title: treasure bran muffins(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 25 minutes.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place chops in glass baking dish and pour marinade over.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 to 6 hours or overnight.
Grill or broil.
Brush occasionally with marinade. You can half the recipe if you want to use 4 thinner chops.

title: fried fish
directions: Mix the buttermilk and lemon juice and dip fish into buttermilk mixture.
Mix the flour and cornmeal and roll fish in flour mixture.
Fry in deep, hot fat until brown, then sprinkle with salt.

title: rhubarb pie(custard)
directions: Cut rhubarb fine.
Mix sugar, flour, salt, beaten egg yolks, milk and melted butter.
Pour over rhubarb which has been placed in unbaked pie shell.
Bake until firm.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Put bacon drippings in skillet.
Combine other ingredients. Stir and cook 8 to 10 minutes until done.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: To crab meat, add crumbs and other ingredients; mix well.
Put into buttered shells or casserole.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until crumbs are delicately browned.
Serve with lemon slices.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix all ingredients except white sugar and nuts. Shape into balls the size of walnuts and dip in white sugar.
Place on cookie sheet, sugared side up.
Top with walnut or pecan half. Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each egg.
Add vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Top with Cool Whip and decorate with shaved chocolate (I use Hershey bar).

title: sugar cut-outs
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix with wooden spoon.
Chill, then roll and cut out in shapes.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Cook pie shells or use graham cracker shells.
Blend cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add Cool whip and bananas, sliced; mix together.
Add to pie shell and top with favorite pie topping.

title: trifle
directions: Cut the cake into 15 to 20 chunks.
Place half the chunks in large bowl.
Pour half the strawberries over the cake.
Spread half the pudding over the strawberries.
Add another layer of cake, strawberries and pudding.
Cover and chill 4 to 6 hours. Spoon on the whipped topping.
Sprinkle with the almonds.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: annie's applesauce meat loaf
directions: Squish up and shape form into loaf pan.

title: minestrone
directions: In a Dutch oven or large, heavy saucepan, saute pork until lightly browned.
Stir in onions and garlic.
Cook until onion is tender, but not browned.
Add spaghetti sauce and next seven ingredients, mixing well.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to medium. Cover and cook one hour.
Stir once or twice.
Add kidney beans and vermicelli.
Simmer 15 minutes longer.
Garnish with parsley and grated cheese.
Makes 8 servings (219 calories per serving).

title: red beans and rice
directions: Place beans in a Dutch oven with water.
Bring to a boil; simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour. Drain and rinse beans.
Return to Dutch oven with broth, garlic and bay leaf; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 1/4 hours.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until beans and vegetables are tender and gravy is thick.
Remove bay leaves.
Serve over rice.
This dish keeps well.
Also good served with corn bread.

title: aunt margie's salad
directions: Whip Dream Whip by directions, omitting vanilla.
Add cheese (whipped), pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
I melt the marshmallows in the pineapple over low heat.
Let set 8 hours.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornmeal and flour.
Add eggs, lemon rind, butter, milk and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients, except rice, in medium saucepan. Simmer 20 minutes, adding water as needed.
Serve over rice. Serves 2 to 3.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa, sugar, eggs and flour.
Beat well. Add pecans and coconut. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread with marshmallow cream while still warm.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add soup, lemon and pepper.
Boil any amount of shrimp.
Mix all above ingredients. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese, green pepper rings and parsley.
Add water to moisten.
Bake in oven 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 12 to 14.

title: sour cream vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Put in refrigerator to set up.

title: turkey stroganoff casserole
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, blend onion, soup, sour cream and milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: caesar salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a jar; shake and refrigerate. Spritz salad with lemon juice.
Add Parmesan cheese and dressing. Toss and add croutons.

title: country kitchen cheese soup
directions: In a large pan, combine potatoes, chicken broth, celery, carrots, onions, parsley, pepper and salt.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes, until tender.
Gradually add milk to flour, stir until blended, then add milk to the vegetables.
Cook until thickened and add ham and cheese.
Stir until blended. Serves 6.

title: seedless grape salad
directions: Toss grapes, celery, cherries, nuts and salad dressing together in bowl. Serve over lettuce leaves.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in two greased loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend oil, sugar and eggs, beating well.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to sugar mixture at intervals.
Add vanilla and chopped apples.
Bake in a well-greased sheet pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes (may take less time).
I have found it only takes about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: patio salad
directions: Cook Minute rice per directions and set aside to cool.
Bring water and salt to boil and add peas.
Do not cook peas too done. Strain in colander and set aside.
Dice up dill pickle, ham and cheese.
Mix all ingredients together with mayonnaise.
Add a little pickle juice to the mixture.
Garnish with tomato wedges and slivers of ham and cheese.
Best served after refrigerating overnight in a sealed container.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; remove stems and set aside.
Melt butter or margarine.
Mix all ingredients into margarine (except mushrooms).
Place mushrooms into baking dish.
Stuff with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until sausage is cooked and browned.

title: no crumb cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour alternately with whipped cream, then vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake
at
for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: "sloppy joes"
directions: Brown hamburger in small amount of fat.
Add onions and celery and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: springtime cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and oranges with electric beater until well mixed.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) cake layers at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Cool.
Cut each layer in half, making 4 layers of cake.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Serve with all kinds of cut-up fresh veggies.

title: beef kabobs with lemon rice
directions: Combine beef and vegetables in plastic Ziploc bag.
Add dressing and marinate 4 to 6 hours in refrigerator.
Alternate beef and vegetables on 4 skewers.
Grill or broil, turning and basting with marinade 5 to 7 minutes or to desired doneness.
Combine rice and remaining ingredients.
Serve kabobs over rice mixture.
Makes 2 servings.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Bring 1-quart water to boil.
Add beans and boil rapidly for 1 minute.
Remove pan from heat and cover.
Let beans stand for 1 hour.
Saute garlic, celery, onions and carrots for
a few minutes, stirring well.
Add tomatoes, broth, salt, pepper, bay leaf and beans.
Heat until soup boils.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until beans are tender.
If soup is being served immediately, stir in cabbage, zucchini and macaroni.
If it is not being served immediately, add macaroni to soup prior to serving. Heat until soup boils.
Remove from heat and discard bay leaf.

title: s'mores
directions: Butter 9-inch square pan.
In large saucepan over low heat, melt oleo and marshmallows.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat; add cereal.
Stir until all pieces are evenly coated.
Press half of cereal mixture into pan with back of buttered spoon.
Place chocolate bars over cereal mix in pan.
Spread remaining cereal mix over chocolate bars.
Cool and cut into bars.
Store in airtight containers.

title: chili
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Add beef and brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer uncovered for 1 hour.

title: pork steak dinner in a dish
directions: Brown pork in 10-inch skillet; drain.
Add potatoes and onion. Mix soup, mushrooms (with liquid), garlic salt, Worcestershire and thyme.
Pour on pork, potatoes and onion.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until tender, 50 to 60 minutes. Rinse frozen peas and carrots under cold water to separate and add to pork and vegetables.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mark's jello
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries, bananas and pineapple.
Pour half of the mixture into a glass 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Let jell.
Cover with 1 pint sour cream, then top with remaining half of Jell-O mixture. Chill until set.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Sift together dry ingredients, except nuts. Mix in a 2-quart bowl the Crisco, egg and water. Add flour mixture and mix well. Drop by teaspoonful about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: rice pudding
directions: Parboil rice.
Drain.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla and cinnamon. Mix thoroughly.
Add raisins.
Add milk.
Mix again.
Add apple. Beat eggs until light and pour over top; blend.
Melt butter in bottom of casserole.
Pour rice mixture into casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: creamy butter
directions: Beat margarine with mixer.
Add oil and buttermilk.
Mix well; refrigerate.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and chopped onions; drain. Drain and rinse all beans EXCEPT chili beans. Combine all ingredients and add seasonings and salt and pepper to your taste. You may want to add water to desired thickness of the chili. Bring to medium heat and then simmer for a minimum of 30 minutes; the longer it simmers, the more the seasoning will be to its full potential.

title: walnut bars
directions: Cream shortening.
Add brown sugar and eggs and mix well.
Add flour, vanilla, soda and salt.
Add water, 1 tablespoon at a time. Put in loaf pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake as you want them.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes around 3 or 4 dozen.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake, covered, 45 minutes at 400°.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Combine the Sugar and Eggs in a large bowl and mix together until mixed well, then add the butter and mix that in, add the 2 cans of pineapple and stir everything together, then add the bread cubes and stir them in until well coated.
Pour into a greased 9x2x13 baking dish and bake in a 350 degree oven for 1 hour until done.

title: beef lombardi
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in chopped tomatoes and next 4 ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomato paste and bay leaf and simmer 30 minutes.
Cook egg noodles and drain.
Stir together noodles, onion and sour cream.
Place noodles in bottom of lightly greased 9x13 in. pan.
top with beef mixture and sprinkle evenly with cheeses.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 more minutes.

title: meringue
directions: Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Fold in confectioners sugar and salt.
Spread over lemon filling. Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes or until the top is lightly browned.

title: lasagna(great for college and high school kids)
directions: Beat eggs and add cottage cheese.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain grease and add spaghetti sauce.

title: ice cream bar dessert
directions: Line a 9x13 pan with 12 ice cream sandwiches. Cover with a layer of cool whip. Drizzle with caramel ice creme topping. Sprinkle with your choice of candy bar. Freeze overnight.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Prepare for frying; salt and pepper.
Roll each piece in self-rising flour, then drop in a pan of water, then roll again in self-rising flour.
Fry in deep fryer until golden brown in Crisco or Wesson oil.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in cold water until crisp.
Wipe dry and slice. Add sliced onions and salt.
Let stand 1 hour; do not drain.
Add 1 quart vinegar and a little water. Boil sugar, mustard seed, ginger root and celery seed for 5 minutes.
While hot, fill jars and seal.

title: chicken divan
directions: In a bowl, mix soup, mayo and lemon juice.
Put 1/2 cup or more on bottom of pan, next broccoli spears, chicken on top of that, then cheese on top of chicken, then the rest of soup mixture.
In a frying pan, melt some oleo and toss croutons.
Put croutons on top of soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with salad, rolls and butter.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and let boil for 3 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until thickened and spoon onto wax paper.

title: banana bread
directions: Blending one at a time, combine the first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Combine flour, soda, salt and baking powder in separate bowl, then add to batter in large bowl.
Thoroughly blend. Add bananas.
(Note:
Bananas should be very ripe!)
Add nuts. Bake in "Pammed" loaf pan (this recipe makes a large loaf) in a preheated 325° to 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Bread is done when top splits and appears thoroughly cooked (but not dried out). Keep covered with aluminum foil to retain freshness.

title: ham and corn chowder
directions: Combine broth, carrot, onion and herbs in pot.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Add remaining ingredients except 1 can potatoes.
Puree can of potatoes and add to mixture.
Bring to a boil and serve.
Serves 4-1 1/2 cup servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all together and chill over night.

title: grasshoppers
directions: Melt over low heat butterscotch morsels.
Stir in chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper to cool.

title: orange fluff
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and orange juice, chilled until partially set.
Fold in oranges.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Beat pudding mix and milk until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread over gelatin.
Chill.

title: alaskan salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix dry jello and Cool Whip well.
Add oranges, pineapple, cottage cheese and nuts.
Mix again.
Refrigerate.

title: rice pudding
directions: In large pot, bring milk to a boil.
Add rice and salt.
Over medium flame, cook milk and rice mixture about 30 minutes.
Stir often to prevent sticking (until rice is cooked).

title: pound cake
directions: Sift the flour.
Cream butter; add sugar and keep adding the following:
Add eggs (1 at a time) and flour (sifted); beat into mixture and add lemon and almond extract.
Cook at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Watch it; time varies.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into serving pieces; brown slowly in two (10-inch) skillets.
Remove from skillets to a baking pan.
Pour fat from skillet, melt margarine in skillet.
Add onion, cook until brown.
Add water, ketchup or barbecue sauce, vinegar, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, dry mustard, salt and pepper; simmer 20 minutes.
Set oven to 350°.
Pour sauce over the ribs.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: southwestern chicken stir fry
directions: Mix lime juice and chili powder in medium glass or plastic bowl. Stir in chicken until well coated. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour. Heat wok or 12 inch skillet over high heat. Add 1 Tbsp. of the oil; rotate wok to coat sides. Add chicken and marinade; stir fry 5 to 6 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink in center. Remove chicken from wok. Add remaining 1 Tbsp. oil to wok; rotate wok to coat sides. Add zucchini and yellow squash; stir fry about 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp tender. Stir in chicken, picante sauce and cilantro. This has 4 grams carbohydrates.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Scramble eggs very well.
Add cream and all other ingredients. Mix well and pour into frozen pie shell.
Place in preheated oven at 350° until center of pie is done, approximately 45 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix beans and mushrooms.
In small bowl, mix cornstarch and mustard, stir in bouillon until smooth. Pour over beans and dot over with margarine.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Place onion rings on top and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and yeast in large bowl.
Gradually add water and oil.
Beat on low with electric mixer.
Scrape bowl and beaters.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in oiled bowl, turning to oil dough.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled.
Punch down and remove from bowl.
Press into a pizza pan.
Form a rim around the edge of the dough and fill the center with desired pizza filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and crumble sausage.
Beat eggs and add all other ingredients.
Line 13 x 9-inch Pyrex pan with bread slices.
Pour other mixture evenly over bread.
Bake at 350° approximately 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together.
Use 2 tablespoons (or to your taste) in cup of hot water.

title: play dough (for children)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in electric skillet on medium heat.
Add oil, water and coloring.
Stir until a ball forms.
Place mixture on waxed paper.
(A drop of clove oil gives a pleasant odor.) Knead it and place in an airtight container.
The kids will play with it for hours!

title: barbecue filling for beef or pork
directions: Cook meat of choice and cut in small chunks; add all ingredients.
Cook to simmer.

title: sausage pizza balls
directions: Combine sausage, cheese, Bisquick, onion and seasoning.
Make into balls.
Bake 10 - 15 minutes at 350 degrees.
May bake the same day or keep in freezer until you want to use them.
Line pan with foil for quick cleanup.

title: gumdrop-marshmallow bars
directions: Heat marshmallows and margarine in 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and cinnamon. Stir in half of the cereal and half of the gumdrops at a time until evenly coated.
Press in buttered square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch). Cool.
Cut into bars, about 2 x 1-inches.
Makes 3 dozen bars.

title: dessert - delicious
directions: Beat cream of tartar, egg whites and vanilla until fluffy. Gradually add the sugar to the ingredients that were beaten.
Fold in broken crackers and add nuts.
Spread on a greased oblong cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Make whipped topping as directed on package.
Spread on cold crust, then top with pie filling.

title: mock sukiyaki
directions: Brown meat in salad oil.
Add vegetables, beef broth and soy sauce.
Cover.
Cook on low until vegetables are tender (10 minutes).
Stir often.
Combine water and cornstarch.
Add to meat. Stir until thick.
Serve over hot rice.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and season with oregano, salt, minced garlic and whole thyme leaves; put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread refried beans over meat; then layers of green chiles and mushrooms and top with cheese and taco sauce.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and spread with sour cream.
Garnish with lots of green onions, olives, avocados, tomatoes, etc.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: bean casserole(quick, easy and good.)
directions: Bake together for 1 hour at 375°.

title: yummy chicken
directions: Cook chicken and remove bones.
Mix mayonnaise, dry mustard and 1 teaspoon dry onion.
Mix bread crumbs and sesame seed.
Dip chicken in mayonnaise mixture, then in crumb mixture.
Lay chicken on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: indian taco
directions: Beat eggs; add milk.
Stir in flour, salt and baking powder and mix well.
Roll out thin on floured board.
Cut or roll to desired shape and size.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef with seasonings, tomato puree and sauce.
Simmer about 25 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions. Alternate in layers in a 2-quart casserole dish the noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Swiss cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza appetizer
directions: Press crescent rolls on bottom of cookie sheet (ungreased) and bake about 15 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, Hidden Valley Ranch dressing and milk. Spread on top of cooled crust.
Top with shredded carrots, onions, broccoli flowers, green pepper, shredded cheese (any kind) or create your own topping.

title: nassawango country club crab dip
directions: In a large bowl, mix cream cheese, sour cream, salad dressing, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, and garlic salt until smooth.
Add enough milk to make mixture creamy.
Stir in 2 tablespoons grated cheese.
Fold crabmeat into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake in preheated 325° oven until mixture is bubbly and brown on top, about 30 minutes.
Makes 4 cups.
Serve with crackers.

title: kielbasa dinner
directions: Bake in a covered pan in a 370° oven for 1 hour or until veggies are tender.

title: oyster cracker mix
directions: Put seasoning in heated oil and pour over crackers; mix thoroughly and set aside.
It will look oily.
Stir them every once in a while and they will lose the oily look.
Be patient, stirring may last two or three hours.
Keep stored in an airtight container.

title: sweet chunk dill pickles
directions: Slice washed pickles chunk-style.
Slice onion and add both to salted water, enough to cover (1 gallon water to 1 cup salt).
Soak overnight.
In morning, drain off water.
Bring fresh water to boil and pour over pickles.
Let cool down.
Drain.
Using a solution of 1 cup water, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup vinegar, bring to boil.
This is your brine.
Fill jars with pickles, onions and dill sprig.
Fill jars with brine.
Add hot sealing caps and lids and tighten.
Jars will seal on towel covered cupboard.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly mix sugars, peanut butter, shortening and eggs. Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Dip a table fork in flour and use to flatten cookies to 2-inch size in crisscross design.
Bake in 375° oven for about 10 minutes, until set but not hard.
Makes about 72 cookies.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour or combine in a food processor.
Mix egg, water and vinegar and pour into shortening-flour mixture. Roll out to form pie crust.
Makes 2 crusts or 1 crust with top.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook ground beef with chopped onions until brown.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, Mexicorn and cooked egg noodles.
Pour into a large casserole dish.
Spread cream of mushroom soup on top.
Cook in oven for 30 minutes at 325°.
Cover with grated Cheddar cheese and cook until cheese is melted.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
May add 1 cup chopped nuts.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: In large skillet brown meat.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir into meat the Lipton soup mix, flour, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: harvest cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg in bowl.
Add shortening, brown sugar, egg and water.
Beat until thoroughly mixed, about 2 minutes.
Stir in apples, rolled oats and raisins. Mixture will be stiff.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon together.
Pat level teaspoon of cookie dough into balls and roll in cinnamon sugar mixture.
Place 1 1/2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: kapusta(polish cabbage soup)
directions: Chop
up cabbage.
Peel and cut potatoes into bite size pieces.
Cut
up
onion.
Combine
cabbage, onion and potatoes into
large
soup
kettle.	Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, garlic powder and salt pork.
Cover with water.
Bring to a boil over medium
heat,
turn
down and simmer for several hours.
Serve with homemade bread.
Even better heated up.
Freezes well.

title: banana pudding layered dessert
directions: Pour graham cracker crumbs over 1 stick melted margarine in
a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs and 2 sticks margarine. Beat with mixer until smooth.
Spread over first layer.
Sprinkle with drained crushed pineapple.
Slice bananas over pineapple. Spread large container Cool Whip over bananas.
Top with candied cherries and chopped nuts.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: lime pie(easy as 1, 2, 3.)
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve soft drink mix in the sweetened condensed milk. Fold in the whipped topping. Spoon into crust; put in refrigerator to chill until set, about 3 hours.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixing bowl, place flour, sugar, shortening, milk, eggs, baking powder, salt, vanilla and water.
Blend for 2 minutes on low speed, then 6 minutes on high. Spoon batter into cupcake pans, filling 1/2 full.
Add 6 to 10 blueberries per cup, mixing them into batter, leaving some on top. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: spice-rubbed mix grill
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients in a small bowl.
Sprinkle the pork, lamb and chicken with salt and then the spice rub.
Transfer to a baking dish and marinate overnight.
Grill.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Sprinkle pumpkin seeds (washed and air-dried) with oil and salt.
Roast in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, watching them carefully in case they get done sooner.

title: italian beef sandwiches
directions: Brown chuck roast. Cover roast with bouillon broth made of 1 broth cube per cup of water. Simmer 3 to 5 hours or until roast falls apart.
(If necessary, add more broth.) Refrigerate. When cooled, remove fat and shred the beef.
Reheat and add the Italian dressing (depends on how spicy you like it) and add more broth, if needed. Serve over warm onion rolls. Serves 6 to 8 plus.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: raspberry delight salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; let stand until solid in an 8 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Place the remaining ingredients in a bowl; allow to stand overnight or several hours.
After jello is set, whip cream mixture to fluffy and spread over jello.

title: pineapple lime salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello and stir.
Add pineapple and nuts. Stir in ice cream.
Pour in loaf pan.

title: curried chicken breasts
directions: Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt and paprika.
Place in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
In small saucepan, drain the liquid from the mushrooms; add chicken bouillon cube.
Heat and stir until bouillon is dissolved.
To the mushroom liquid, add sliced mushrooms, Sauterne, minced onion, curry powder and pepper. Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes more.

title: monkey bread
directions: Over medium heat, melt oleo in milk.
Mix yeast and water in a small mixing bowl.
Mix salt, sugar and flour in a large mixing bowl.
Add yeast and milk mixtures to flour mixture.
Mix well. Cover with a cloth and let rise for 2 hours.
Knead dough.
Cut in strips; dip each strip in melted butter.
Arrange in tube pan. Cover and let rise 2 more hours when doubled.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Stew hen until tender; reserve 4 cups broth.
Cut meat into bite-size pieces; set aside.
Heat butter in saucepan and gradually blend in flour.
Slowly add 4 cups broth, then cream. Stir over low heat until mixture has thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: percolator punch
directions: Put sugar, cloves, cinnamon and salt in basket.
Put liquids in percolator.
Perk!

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add all the vegetables at once and saute until soft, but not brown.
Add flour and stir to combine.
Cook until it begins to turn a light brown color.

title: jiffy lemon cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly.
Add lemon and pineapple flavors and stir in dry ingredients and milk.
Grease and flour cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp fettucini
directions: Melt oleo and saute onions, celery and bell peppers.
Cover for 15 minutes.
Keep pot covered throughout whole top-of-stove cooking.
Add flour and cook 15 minutes, stirring often.
Add cream, Velveeta cheese, garlic, seasonings and shrimp.
Cook over low heat 30 minutes.
Boil noodles.
Drain.
Combine noodles and shrimp mixture, mixing well.
Pour into greased dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb-custard pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Add to egg and milk. Stir in rhubarb.
Place in pastry-lined pan and dot with oleo. Cover with lattice crust and bake 50 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: heavenly hot chocolate sauce
directions: Melt butter in a double boiler.
Drop in chocolate and melt. Add sugar gradually and stir.
(It's going to be super hard to stir!)
Add salt.
Slowly add milk, a little at a time.
Serve hot or cold over ice cream.

title: the best russian tea
directions: Combine
spices
in
gallon
water and slowly boil about 10 minutes.
Strain and pour over sugar while hot.	Pour this mixture over tea and let steep.
Strain again and add 1/2 gallon cold water.
Mix with juices.
Serve hot or cold.

title: bethany's best brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients on low speed until mixed. Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 22 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Melt butter; add flour and milk and bring to boil, then add broth and 1 cup chicken.
Pour mixture into oblong dish.
Top with 1 cup chicken.
Top this with biscuits rolled thin.
Bake until biscuits are done at 400° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: scrambled egg and ham pie
directions: In a bowl, beat 12 eggs with milk, cream, salt and pepper. In a large skillet, toss 3/4 cup ham in 3 tablespoons butter over moderately high heat for 1 or 2 minutes.
Add half the egg mixture and cook it over moderate heat, stirring constantly, for 1 or 2 minutes.
Remove the pan from the heat, still stirring, and stir the eggs until they are only very lightly set.
Pour the scrambled eggs and ham into a well buttered 11-inch flameproof glass pie plate.

title: gels cream
directions: Prepare jello according to directions.
Allow to cool in refrigerator until the consistency of thick cream.
Allow ice cream to soften at room temperature, but not melted.
Beat ice cream and jello together in a large bowl until thoroughly combined.
Put back in refrigerator until completely set.
Serve in sherbet bowls.
Top with whipped cream if desired.
Serves 6 people.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add mayonnaise to jello while still hot.
Scrape fat from corned beef and crumble into small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients to warm jello mixture, except sliced hard-cooked eggs.
Use two foil pans (11 5/8 x
1/4 x 2 3/8-inches).
Divide half of the mixture between the two pans. Top with sliced hard-cooked eggs.
Pour remaining jello mixture between pans.
It will set up quickly.
Make a day ahead.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: chicken strips
directions: Shake chicken strips, flour, salt and pepper in a bag.
Brown in oil and drain.
Combine 2 cups hot water, chicken bouillon cubes and 2 sticks butter.
Add to strips.
Simmer strips in uncovered pan for 25 minutes.
During the last 15 minutes, add 1/2 cup wine and garlic powder.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Cut mincemeat up; add soda and boiling water.
Let cool; add eggs, sugar, salt and butter, then add flour.
Bake in a moderate oven (not hot).

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil (slowly) chicken in the water for 40 to 45 minutes. Remove chicken from water.
Set aside on platter to cool.
Skim top of the water and discard skimmings.
Add vegetables to water (can be cut first if you wish) and bouillon cube.
When the chicken has cooled, remove meat from bone and put back in water to simmer for 2 more hours.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Cook and drain shells. Prepare stuffing mix and add chicken and mayonnaise. Stuff shells with mixture and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover with soup mixed with water or broth from the cooked chicken. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 45-60 minutes until soup is bubbly.

title: dream shake
directions: Whirl ingredients in blender.
Drink away!
This is a good, low-fat pick-me-up.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallow cream in oil in a double boiler, stirring until blended.

title: dump cake
directions: Use a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine
potatoes, 1/2 cup margarine, onion, soup, sour cream and
cheese.
Stir	well
and
spoon into greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.

title: wild grape jelly(makes 4 to 5 pints)
directions: Boil fruit (ground or vine variety) in large saucepan, adding water to just cover fruit.
After squeezing and straining juice, measure 4 cups juice, sugar, lemon juice, Certo and margarine or butter.

title: cheesy brat stew
directions: Cut brats in 1/2-inch pieces.
Place in large skillet with potatoes (cubed), beans (drained), onion, cheese, soup and water. Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: coq au vin(chicken casserole; serves 6)
directions: *Use 1 bay leaf, 1 sprig thyme, 1 sprig rosemary and 8 sprigs parsley.

title: lemon salad
directions: Prepare jello using 2 cups boiling water. Drain pineapple. Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13 pan. Refrigerate until set. Cut into squares to serve. Keeps very well in refrigerator.

title: turkey joes
directions: Brown margarine and ground turkey.
Stir in onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook until tender over low heat.
Mix in condensed tomato soup, barbecue sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 30 minutes over low heat.
Serve on buns.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles, and place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for one hour.
Top with noodles and bake, uncovered, 10 minutes longer.

title: frosted daiquiri pie
directions: In double boiler top pan, combine gelatin with 2/3 cup sugar and salt; add egg yolks, water and lime juice and beat until blended.
Cook over boiling water, stirring, until the mixture coats a spoon.
Remove from heat.
Tint pale green with food color.
When the mixture is cool, stir in the rum.
Refrigerate until the mixture is slightly thicker than unbeaten egg whites.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain water.
Cook cream and Cheez Whiz together over low heat.
Stir constantly until Cheez Whiz mixture is creamy and smooth.
Melt butter and crumble crackers in butter. Add cooked broccoli to Cheez Whiz mixture.
Stir well.
Pour into long baking dish.
Sprinkle crushed buttered crumbs over top of broccoli.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: light batter for vegetables or meat
directions: In bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients.
Add water and egg; stir until smooth.
Pour 1 quart corn oil into large skillet to depth of 1/2, filling no more than 1/3 full.
Heat over medium heat to 375°.
Dip 4 cups cut up vegetables as zucchini, carrots, onions and mushrooms or 1 boneless, skinless chicken breast, a few at a time.
Add vegetables or meat to oil.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes, turning once.
Brown and then drain.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat, onion and garlic until gray.
Drain.
Add other ingredients and simmer until real hot.
Pour in greased casserole and put grated cheese and Fritos on top.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: sweet sour chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces, skin down, in shallow baking dish (12-cup size).
Drain pineapple; reserve 2 tablespoons juice. Combine cornstarch, reserved pineapple juice, sugar, soy sauce, vinegar, garlic, ginger and pepper in large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens and bubbles.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 30 minutes, basting several times.
Turn chicken, spread with pineapple, spoon sauce all over.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until tender.

title: fluffy pudding frosting
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix and sugar.
Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cakes immediately.
Store frosted cakes in fridge.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish. Use the back side of a spoon to make spreading easier.
Spread chili over cream cheese.
Shred Monterey Jack cheese over chili. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 5 minutes. Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli and potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Cover with water.
Boil until tender. Leave water.
Add broccoli, sour cream, Velveeta, butter, salt, pepper and garlic salt and stir until all is melted and broccoli is tender.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg until fluffy. Beat in remaining ingredients until smooth. Cook on hot greased griddle until golden brown.

title: frozen salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese with 2 tablespoons pineapple juice. Add mayonnaise and other ingredients.
Freeze.

title: mexican "fudge"
directions: Spread 1/2 the cheese in an 11 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine eggs and green sauce; spread evenly over cheese.
Add remaining cheese to cover mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into 1-inch squares and serve hot.
Great appetizers!

title: crab-shrimp bake
directions: Turn into
quart
casserole	or
individual	bakers. Combine 1 cup
soft
bread	crumbs	with
1 tablespoon butter, melted.
Sprinkle atop
casserole.	Bake
at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for casserole,
20 to 25 minutes for individual bakers or until hot.	Serves 4.

title: sugar-free cookies
directions: Put dates, raisins, prunes and water in pan.
Boil until thick.
Add oleo and let cool.
Beat eggs and rest of ingredients. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: platte county pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs in medium bowl.
Add flour and sugar and continue beating 2 minutes.
Add vanilla, butter, nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 60 minutes. Serve warm or at room temperature with whipped cream.

title: mama's stuffed bell peppers(spicy version!)
directions: In skillet, brown meat and cook onion until done; drain. Cook rice (about 20 minutes) according to package directions. Halve pepper, remove seeds and boil until slightly tender, about 8 minutes. Place in a casserole dish. Add seasonings, meat, rice and all ingredients (except Cheddar cheese) together and mix well; should be moist. Stuff peppers. Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cho tho tho cookies(italian)
directions: Mix dry ingredients first.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls about 1-inch rounds.
Does not rise too much.
Bake at 325° for 18 minutes or brown a little on the bottom.
When cool frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: pickled zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini into 1-inch chunks and thinly slice onion.
In 2-quart saucepan, heat sugar, vinegar, pickling spice and bay leaves to boiling.
Add sliced onion.
Cook for 1 minute.
Place zucchini in small glass jars or plastic container.
Pour liquid over and refrigerate.
Drain before serving.
Serve with grilled steak, chicken or hamburger.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: christmas gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes 30 minutes or until done.
Peel and shred potatoes.
Mix all ingredients.

title: spinach dip
directions: Put all in blender and process.
Serve with vegetables.

title: candied yams
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes and cook until it begins to thicken.
Pour over sweet potatoes and bake.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in flour and vanilla.
Add pecans and mix.
If mixture is too stiff, add a tablespoon of water.
Shape into 3/4 to 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until light brown at 350°.
Cool 5 minutes.
Roll in additional powdered sugar while still warm.

title: halloween greasepaint
directions: Using a rubber spatula, blend first 3 ingredients on a white plate to form a smooth paste.
Add 3 to 4 drops glycerin for a creamy consistency.
The yield should be enough for a child's face.
If you need more, make the amount you need before adding coloring, then add food coloring, a drop at the time, blending after each drop, until you have desired shade.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into small ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 1 cup.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour in an unbaked pie crust. Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Real easy and good.

title: old virginia wassail
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a simmer. Strain out cinnamon stick and cloves. Serve hot.

title: spinach pie
directions: Chop, wash and drain spinach.
Fry onion in butter until golden brown.
Add to spinach the beaten eggs and crumbled Feta cheese.
Mix all ingredients well.
Brush layers of filo with melted butter.
Place at least 6 layers on bottom of pan.
Spread spinach mixture, and so on, until pan is full.
Put 5 layers on top, all spread with melted butter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, until golden brown on top.

title: pickled eggs
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, water, pickling spice and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove pickling spice and discard.
Stir food coloring over eggs in jar and cover.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours. Remove from liquid to serve.

title: straw-ba-nut ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and salt until foamy.
Add sugar gradually.
Mix well.
Add whipping cream and vanilla.
(Mixture will be thick.) Add fruits and pecans.
Pour into freezer.
Finish filling freezer with milk.
Stir mixture thoroughly.
Freeze in electric or hand cranked freezer.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and core apples, cut in pieces.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Open can of rolls and separate.
Roll out thin.
Place apples on roll.
Completely cover with dough. Place dumplings in baking dish.

title: baked squash with apples
directions: Cut squash into chunks or slices. Combine with apples, raisins and lemon juice in an 8-cup buttered baking dish (9 x 9-inch pan). Sprinkle with cinnamon. Dot with margarine.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until squash is tender.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Combine the milk, almond extract, pudding and Cool Whip.
Combine the two mixtures. Alternate layers of Oreos and creamed mixture, starting with Oreos.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Cut asparagus in 1 1/2-inch pieces; place in saucepan with just enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cook until tender, 4 or 5 minutes. Pour off hot water; rinse asparagus in cold water to stop cooking.
Place in large plastic bowl.

title: fried vegetables
directions: Dredge vegetables in flour.
Cook in fat over low to medium heat, until tender and lightly browned.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve over ice.
Serves about 35. Triple recipe for 100 people.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter;
add
flour
which
has
been sifted with baking powder.
Add
flavoring.
Beat
eggs
and add sugar and continue beating until satin smooth.
Add to flour mixture and beat for 3 to	5
minutes.
Bake
in a tube pan which has been greased on the bottom only and lightly floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour
and 15 minutes.
Let stand on rack for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, apricot nectar, evaporated milk and peaches in mixing bowl.
Pour into freezer and finish filling with 1% or skim milk to make a gallon of ice cream.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients before baking.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sharp Cheddar cheese on top.
Also 1/2 cup croutons.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin choco-dot cake(moist, sweet and healthful)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs until foamy and add pumpkin, oil and All-Bran.
Mix well.
Add flour mixture and stir until combined.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread in ungreased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Drizzle with sugar glaze or sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 325° in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and salt.
Boil for 15 minutes or until soft ball forms.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased pan.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Beat cream cheese, egg, sugar and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips and set aside.
May want to double the second mixture.
Sift together the dry ingredients and beat together all the ingredients.
Fill small cake liners with second mixture and then drop 1/2 teaspoon of first mixture on top of each.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: potato and cheese casserole
directions: Spread butter over a 9-inch pie plate.
Grate potatoes and drain well.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon of salt and chopped onion; mix well.
Press over bottom and sides of pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars.
Add egg and beat well.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into rolls.
Roll in waxed paper.
Chill several hours or overnight. Slice thin and bake on a greased cookie sheet at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon, and nutmeg to mixture, alternately with milk and flavoring.
Add mixture to fruit and nuts and mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake for 20 minutes at 300°.
Makes 70-80 cookies.
An ice cream scoop works well to shape cookies.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Separate the eggs and beat the yellow of eggs with the sugar. Mix the cocoa with a little warm water; add this to the eggs and sugar.
Stir it the cornstarch next and then add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Add a little cold water to the egg whites and beat until stiff.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar (one at a time) and beat.
Put meringue on top of pie and brown.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: In large bowl, combine Jell-O and boiling water.
Fold in thawed strawberries and juice, crushed pineapple and half the juice, mashed bananas and chopped nuts.
Pour half into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and save juice.
Use juice in the puddings and cook until clear and thick.
When cool, mix with the fruit.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Blend in blender the eggs, cream, Bisquick and seasonings for 1 minute.
Pour over cheese, bacon, etc.
Sprinkle top with paprika and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
May check at 45 minutes or when top cracks.
Good Luck!

title: mexican caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients except avocado.
Chill 4 to 5 hours (or overnight).
Add avocado and serve with Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: three bean salad
directions: Using
refrigerated
(canned) biscuits, form each individual biscuit into
a
(stick) about 4 to 5 inches long.
Dip each stick in
milk and roll in sesame seeds.
Bake in oven at 400° until light golden brown.

title: blueberry yogurt pie
directions: Combine the yogurt, pudding mix (the powder only) and lemon rind in a small bowl. Chill, uncovered, in the refrigerator for 5 minutes. Spoon the mixtures into the pie shell, then arrange the blueberries on top. Warm the jelly in a small heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring often until melted, 2 minutes. Brush over the blueberries. Chill the pie, uncovered, in the refrigerator for 1 hour or until firm. Serves 8.

title: mom's peach pudding pie
directions: Place peaches into a well buttered 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and flour. Sprinkle over peaches and then dot with butter.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix together meat, spices, rice and egg.
Shape into 2 ounce balls.
Soften cabbage in hot water.
Roll each ball in 1 cabbage leaf.
Layer cabbage rolls and sauerkraut.
Pour tomato puree over rolls.
Add water or sauerkraut juice to 1-inch deep.
Cover and bake at 350° for at least 1 1/2 hours.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Toss potatoes with butter and salt; arrange on the bottom and up the sides of a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are almost tender.

title: ann's artichoke dip
directions: In Pyrex dish, mix ingredients.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown onion, garlic and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add prime stake, water from mushrooms and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles; arrange in buttered baking dish.
Layer noodles, sliced cheeses and sauce mixture.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, ending with sauce.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 8 large servings.

title: baked chicken breasts with gruyere and mushrooms
directions: Cut boned breasts into strips.
Marinate in egg and salt mixture for 1 hour.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs to coat.
Brown lightly in butter in small pan.
Transfer to 1 1/2-quart casserole, slice mushrooms over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over mushrooms.
Pour chicken stock over the entire dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Pour fresh lemon juice over casserole just before serving.

title: jelly cake
directions: Mix all together as directed for cake mix; make 3 layers. When cooled, spread apple jelly and sprinkle coconut on each layer.
Repeat.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine melted butter and graham cracker crumbs in bowl; mix well. Pat into 9 x 13-inch dish. Mix eggs, softened butter and confectioners sugar in mixer bowl. Beat at high speed with electric mixer for 5 minutes. Spread over crust. Layer pineapple and bananas over filling. Spread whipped topping over fruit. Drizzle chocolate sauce over top. Sprinkle with nuts and cherries. Chill in refrigerator for 4 hours to overnight. Yields 12 servings.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Whip softened cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar until smooth. Pour into pie crust.
Chill.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream oleo.
Add sugars, then peanut butter.
Beat until well blended.
Add egg; continue to beat.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press down with a fork; bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bratwurst stew
directions: Simmer slow 30 minutes.
Will make its own juice.
Do not add more water.

title: sausage bits
directions: Brown and drain sausage; dissolve bouillon cube in water and combine with sausage and remaining ingredients.
Shape into bite size pieces and bake on a lightly greased baking sheet for 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Serve hot.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Spread out crescent rolls into a rectangle (do not separate into individuals).
Brush melted butter over the rectangle. Combine cinnamon and sugar in a bowl and sprinkle over buttered dough.
Roll the dough lengthwise.
Cut the roll into 1/2-inch slices.
Bake rolls at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.
Pour icing over rolls and serve.

title: cheddar carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender (crisp). Saute onion in butter. Add carrots and rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in airtight jar.
Use 3 or 4 teaspoons or to suit your taste for each cup of hot water.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding with drained juices and add other ingredients. One-fourth teaspoon of poppy seed can be added.

title: texas tortillas
directions: Mix all ingredients (except tortillas and picante sauce) until smooth.
Spread mixture on tortillas and roll up.
Wrap tortillas in damp paper towels and place in Ziploc baggies.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: raspberry cream pie
directions: Mix and put 1 tablespoon sugar and flour into bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Beat egg and add cornstarch, 3/4 cup sugar and milk.
Put into shell.
Drop raspberries on top.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: homestyle vegetables
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole dish, covered in the water, cook on High power for 7 to 9 minutes until vegetables are crisp and tender, stirring once.
Add salad dressing; toss gently to coat.
Cook, covered, on High about 1 minute or until heated through.

title: christmas rainbow poke cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Bake as directed in 2 cake pans; cool 10 minutes.
Place cake layers, top side up, back in 2 clean pans; prick each with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over raspberry Jell-O in bowl, stir until dissolved. Spoon raspberry over 1 layer.
Repeat with lime Jell-O. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Dip 1 layer in pan into warm water 10 seconds; invert on plate gently shaking to loosen.
Remove from pan, spread layer with 1 cup Cool Whip.
Remove remaining layer same way; place on top of first layer.
Frost with Cool Whip. Refrigerate; garnish with flattened gumdrops, cut to look like holly.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat.
Add water.
Bring to boil.
Add celery, onions and soy sauce; boil for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add cornstarch and sesame oil.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry bread #1
directions: Blend together the first 8 ingredients.
Then to the juice and pulp of 1 orange or 2/3 cup orange juice, add butter or margarine and enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
Add to dry ingredients, blending with a fork until moistened.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hummus dip
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender or food processor.
Finely chopped vegetables (onion, carrot, green pepper, etc.) may be added.
Serve with crackers.

title: amaretto punch
directions: Combine juice, pop and Amaretto.
Then spoon in sherbet.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Into stiffly beaten egg whites, fold in remaining ingredients.
Line baking sheet with aluminum foil and grease it.
Drop cookies onto foil and place in oven.
Turn oven off and forget about cookies until morning (don't open oven door until then).
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: cracklin' corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk and milk; stir well.
Add shortening and cracklings.
Stir well.
Pour batter into a hot, greased 9-inch cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini pizza pie
directions: Shredded zucchini makes a colorful, moist foundation for pizza topping.

title: mints
directions: Mix well.
Add food coloring and 2 drops peppermint flavoring. Coconut or almonds may be used.
Place in molds to form mints.

title: louisiana cajun fried turkey
directions: Mix together the garlic, onion, sauces, seasoning and lemon juice; dilute with water in bowl.
Inject turkey all over with seasonings (legs, thighs, breast, etc.).
Allow turkey to thaw for easier injections.
Inject 10 to 12 hours prior to cooking. Thoroughly sprinkle Tony's seasoning in cavity and all outside areas of the turkey after injections.
Go ahead and ask your wife to buy you a cooking thermometer.
You'll need it!

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half of cake in pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Dip biscuits in mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Stack the biscuits in tube pan.
Mix brown sugar and melted margarine; pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes, then turn over.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight or at least 3 hours.
Serve with raw vegetables as dip.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Mix hash browns, 1 cup butter, cream of chicken soup, Cheddar cheese, sour cream and onions.
Top with corn flakes and drizzle 1/2 cup melted butter on top.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a separate bowl, mix shortening, sugar, eggs and bananas, then mix together with flour mixture.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat together well the eggs and milk.
Mix all ingredients together, put in casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Combine cocoa, 1 cup water and margarine.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Mix flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Stir in eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add cocoa mixture; stir until blended.
Put in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch greased pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: batter bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add milk and last, add egg. Bake in well-greased, preheated pan.
Preheat stove and bake at 450° until brown.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Blend flour, brown sugar and margarine until coarse crumbs. Add nuts.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325° on cookie sheet, stirring every 5 minutes.
Allow to cool and spread in bottom of 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: paper cup frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Spoon into paper muffin cups.
Freeze.
Remove from tin 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 24.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Thaw and mash strawberries.
Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries, which have been sweetened with 2 packages sugar substitute.
Add pineapple and bananas.

title: season-all salt
directions: Use 4 parts of water to 1 part of sugar.
Boil water; add sugar and stir well and cool.
Red food coloring is not necessary if the feeder is red or has red flowers through which the birds take the syrup.
Some don't use the red coloring for hummers since the controversy over red dye.

title: breakfast brownie
directions: In blender, put egg in first until smooth.
Mix all together. Use an 8 x 8-inch pan; coat pan with fat-free oil.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Whole portion is 1/4 regular bread (1/8 if diet bread), 1/2 fruit and 1 milk.

title: crunchy peanut butter bars
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup over moderate heat in a 3 quart saucepan until mixture boils.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Add Rice Krispies to mixture.
Mix well.
Press mixture into pan and cool.
Melt chocolate bars and butterscotch pieces together and stir until well blended.
Spread evenly over cereal mix.
Cool. Cut into squares (48 to 64 pieces).
